{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848151127,"sessionID":"ses_287348949ffemSMrps0exZh022","part":{"id":"prt_d78cc545c001jub3CkgUPeD5s5","messageID":"msg_d78cc449d001V8GegtnLJmzqBm","sessionID":"ses_287348949ffemSMrps0exZh022","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_37280d77cff941338f4591e6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-016: PicoD File Management API вҖ” Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: The `pkg/picod/files/` subpackage provides a comprehensive file management API for the PicoD in-sandbox daemon. It replaces the monolithic `files.go` with a structured subpackage that exports a `FileManager` interface and individual HTTP handlers for read, write, stat, list, upload, download, delete, move, mkdir, search, and chmod operations. All operations are constrained within a workspace jail via path sanitization and protected by JWT authentication.\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 Route Reorganization\n10: \n11: The file management routes are reorganized from legacy wildcard/overloaded paths to explicit sub-paths under `/api/files/`:\n12: \n13: ```\n14: Legacy (AR-015)                  вҶ’  AR-016\n15: в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n16: POST /api/files (upload)         вҶ’  POST /api/files/upload\n17: GET  /api/files (list)           вҶ’  GET  /api/files (with ?path query)\n18: GET  /api/files/*path (download) вҶ’  GET  /api/files/download?path=...\n19:                                   +  POST /api/files/read\n20:                                   +  POST /api/files/write\n21:                                   +  GET  /api/files/stat?path=...\n22:                                   +  POST /api/files/delete\n23:                                   +  POST /api/files/move\n24:                                   +  POST /api/files/mkdir\n25:                                   +  POST /api/files/search\n26:                                   +  POST /api/files/chmod\n27: ```\n28: \n29: ### 1.3 Data Flow\n30: \n31: ```\n32: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n33: в”Ӯ                    Client (Router/SDK)                        в”Ӯ\n34: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n35:                          в”Ӯ JWT-protected HTTP\n36:                          в–ј\n37: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n38: в”Ӯ                     Gin Engine (/api)                         в”Ӯ\n39: в”Ӯ              AuthMiddleware (JWT RS256 verify)                в”Ӯ\n40: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n41:                          в”Ӯ\n42:                          в–ј\n43: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n44: в”Ӯ                   FileHandler (server.go)                     в”Ӯ\n45: в”Ӯ      Routes to files/ subpackage handlers via FileManager     в”Ӯ\n46: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n47:                          в”Ӯ\n48:                          в–ј\n49: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n50: в”Ӯ                    FileManager                                в”Ӯ\n51: в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ\n52: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ Read    в”Ӯ Write    в”Ӯ Stat     в”Ӯ List     в”Ӯ Upload      в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\n53: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ Downloadв”Ӯ Delete   в”Ӯ Move     в”Ӯ MkDir    в”Ӯ Search      в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\n54: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ Chmod   в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ             в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\n55: в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ\n56: в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ         в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ            в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ\n57: в”Ӯ       в–ј         в–ј          в–ј          в–ј            в–ј          в”Ӯ\n58: в”Ӯ  sanitizePath вҶ’ workspace jail вҶ’ os.* operations              в”Ӯ\n59: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n60:                          в”Ӯ\n61:                          в–ј\n62: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n63: в”Ӯ               Filesystem (sandbox workspace)                  в”Ӯ\n64: в”Ӯ         workspaceDir (config.Workspace, resolved abs)         в”Ӯ\n65: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n66: ```\n67: \n68: ### 1.4 Package Layout\n69: \n70: ```\n71: pkg/picod/\n72: в”ңв”Җв”Җ server.go              вҖ” Server struct, route registration (updated)\n73: в”ңв”Җв”Җ config.go              вҖ” Config struct (extended with file management fields)\n74: в”ңв”Җв”Җ types.go               вҖ” ExecuteRequest/Response, legacy types (retained)\n75: в”ңв”Җв”Җ auth.go                вҖ” AuthManager (unchanged)\n76: в”ңв”Җв”Җ execute.go             вҖ” ExecuteHandler (unchanged)\n77: в”ңв”Җв”Җ files/                 вҖ” New file management subpackage\n78: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ manager.go         вҖ” FileManager interface + implementation\n79: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ types.go           вҖ” Request/Response structs, constants\n80: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ sanitize.go        вҖ” sanitizePath (migrated from files.go)\n81: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ read.go            вҖ” ReadFileHandler\n82: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ write.go           вҖ” WriteFileHandler\n83: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ stat.go            вҖ” StatFileHandler\n84: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ list.go            вҖ” ListFilesHandler (migrated from AR-015)\n85: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ upload.go          вҖ” UploadFileHandler (migrated, with chunk support)\n86: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ download.go        вҖ” DownloadFileHandler (migrated, with Range support)\n87: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ delete.go          вҖ” DeleteFileHandler\n88: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ move.go            вҖ” MoveFileHandler\n89: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ mkdir.go           вҖ” MkDirHandler\n90: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ search.go          вҖ” SearchFilesHandler\n91: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ chmod.go           вҖ” ChmodHandler\n92: в”ңв”Җв”Җ server_test.go         вҖ” Server-level tests (updated routes)\n93: в”ңв”Җв”Җ config_test.go         вҖ” Config parsing tests (updated)\n94: в”ңв”Җв”Җ auth_test.go           вҖ” Auth tests (unchanged)\n95: в”ңв”Җв”Җ execute_test.go        вҖ” Execute tests (unchanged)\n96: в”ңв”Җв”Җ sanitize_test.go       вҖ” Path sanitization tests (moved to files/)\n97: в”ңв”Җв”Җ health_test.go         вҖ” Health check tests (unchanged)\n98: в””в”Җв”Җ files/                 вҖ” File subpackage tests\n99:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ manager_test.go    вҖ” FileManager integration tests\n100:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ sanitize_test.go   вҖ” Path sanitization tests\n101:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ read_test.go       вҖ” ReadFile tests\n102:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ write_test.go      вҖ” WriteFile tests\n103:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ stat_test.go       вҖ” StatFile tests\n104:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ list_test.go       вҖ” ListFiles tests\n105:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ upload_test.go     вҖ” Upload tests (incl. chunked)\n106:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ download_test.go   вҖ” Download tests (incl. Range)\n107:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ delete_test.go     вҖ” Delete tests (incl. batch)\n108:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ move_test.go       вҖ” Move tests\n109:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ mkdir_test.go      вҖ” MkDir tests\n110:     в”ңв”Җв”Җ search_test.go     вҖ” Search tests\n111:     в””в”Җв”Җ chmod_test.go      вҖ” Chmod tests\n112: ```\n113: \n114: ### 1.5 Dependencies\n115: \n116: | Module | Purpose |\n117: |--------|---------|\n118: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework, request binding |\n119: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n120: | `encoding/base64` | Base64 encoding/decoding for read/write |\n121: | `path/filepath` | Path manipulation, sanitization |\n122: | `os` | File system operations |\n123: | `io`, `mime`, `net/http` | File serving, content type detection |\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ## 2. Data Structures\n128: \n129: ### 2.1 Config Extension\n130: \n131: ```go\n132: type Config struct {\n133:     Port             int    `json:\"port\"`\n134:     Workspace        string `json:\"workspace\"`\n135:     MaxChunkSize     int64  `json:\"max_chunk_size\"`      // default: 32 << 20 (32 MiB)\n136:     MaxBatchSize     int    `json:\"max_batch_size\"`      // default: 100\n137:     MaxSearchResults int    `json:\"max_search_results\"`  // default: 100\n138:     MaxSearchDepth   int    `json:\"max_search_depth\"`    // default: 50\n139: }\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### 2.2 FileManager Interface\n143: \n144: ```go\n145: type FileManager interface {\n146:     ReadFile(ctx context.Context, req *ReadFileRequest) (*ReadFileResponse, error)\n147:     WriteFile(ctx context.Context, req *WriteFileRequest) (*WriteFileResponse, error)\n148:     StatFile(ctx context.Context, path string) (*StatFileResponse, error)\n149:     ListFiles(ctx context.Context, path string) (*ListFilesResponse, error)\n150:     UploadFile(ctx context.Context, req *UploadFileRequest) (*FileInfo, error)\n151:     UploadFileChunked(ctx context.Context, req *ChunkedUploadRequest) (*FileInfo, error)\n152:     DownloadFile(ctx context.Context, req *DownloadFileRequest) (*DownloadFileResponse, error)\n153:     DeleteFile(ctx context.Context, req *DeleteFileRequest) (*DeleteFileResponse, error)\n154:     MoveFile(ctx context.Context, req *MoveFileRequest) (*MoveFileResponse, error)\n155:     MkDir(ctx context.Context, req *MkDirRequest) (*MkDirResponse, error)\n156:     SearchFiles(ctx context.Context, req *SearchFilesRequest) (*SearchFilesResponse, error)\n157:     Chmod(ctx context.Context, req *ChmodRequest) (*ChmodResponse, error)\n158: }\n159: ```\n160: \n161: ### 2.3 Request/Response Types (`files/types.go`)\n162: \n163: ```go\n164: type ReadFileRequest struct {\n165:     Path   string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n166:     Offset int64  `json:\"offset\"`\n167:     Limit  int64  `json:\"limit\"`\n168: }\n169: \n170: type ReadFileResponse struct {\n171:     Content   string `json:\"content\"`\n172:     TotalSize int64  `json:\"total_size\"`\n173:     ReadBytes int64  `json:\"read_bytes\"`\n174: }\n175: \n176: type WriteFileRequest struct {\n177:     Path         string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n178:     Content      string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n179:     Offset       int64  `json:\"offset\"`\n180:     Mode         string `json:\"mode\"`\n181:     CreateParent bool   `json:\"create_parent\"`\n182: }\n183: \n184: type WriteFileResponse struct {\n185:     Path         string `json:\"path\"`\n186:     Size         int64  `json:\"size\"`\n187:     BytesWritten int64  `json:\"bytes_written\"`\n188: }\n189: \n190: type StatFileResponse struct {\n191:     Name      string    `json:\"name\"`\n192:     Size      int64     `json:\"size\"`\n193:     Mode      string    `json:\"mode\"`\n194:     ModTime   time.Time `json:\"mod_time\"`\n195:     IsDir     bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n196:     IsSymlink bool      `json:\"is_symlink\"`\n197: }\n198: \n199: type ListFilesResponse struct {\n200:     Files []FileEntry `json:\"files\"`\n201: }\n202: \n203: type FileEntry struct {\n204:     Name     string    `json:\"name\"`\n205:     Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n206:     Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n207:     Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n208:     IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n209: }\n210: \n211: type UploadFileRequest struct {\n212:     Path    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n213:     Content string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n214:     Mode    string `json:\"mode\"`\n215: }\n216: \n217: type ChunkedUploadRequest struct {\n218:     Path       string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n219:     Content    string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n220:     Mode       string `json:\"mode\"`\n221:     ChunkIndex int    `json:\"chunk_index\"`\n222:     ChunkTotal int    `json:\"chunk_total\"`\n223: }\n224: \n225: type DownloadFileRequest struct {\n226:     Path  string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n227:     Range string `json:\"-\"` // from HTTP Range header\n228: }\n229: \n230: type DownloadFileResponse struct {\n231:     Content       []byte\n232:     ContentType   string\n233:     ContentLength int64\n234:     StatusCode    int // 200 or 206\n235:     ContentRange  string\n236: }\n237: \n238: type DeleteFileRequest struct {\n239:     Path  string   `json:\"path\"`\n240:     Paths []string `json:\"paths\"`\n241: }\n242: \n243: type DeleteFileResponse struct {\n244:     Deleted []string        `json:\"deleted\"`\n245:     Failed  []DeleteFailure `json:\"failed\"`\n246: }\n247: \n248: type DeleteFailure struct {\n249:     Path  string `json:\"path\"`\n250:     Error string `json:\"error\"`\n251: }\n252: \n253: type MoveFileRequest struct {\n254:     Source      string `json:\"source\" binding:\"required\"`\n255:     Destination string `json:\"destination\" binding:\"required\"`\n256: }\n257: \n258: type MoveFileResponse struct {\n259:     Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n260:     Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n261: }\n262: \n263: type MkDirRequest struct {\n264:     Path string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n265:     Mode string `json:\"mode\"`\n266: }\n267: \n268: type MkDirResponse struct {\n269:     Path    string `json:\"path\"`\n270:     Created bool   `json:\"created\"`\n271: }\n272: \n273: type SearchFilesRequest struct {\n274:     Path       string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n275:     Pattern    string `json:\"pattern\" binding:\"required\"`\n276:     MaxResults int    `json:\"max_results\"`\n277: }\n278: \n279: type SearchFilesResponse struct {\n280:     Matches   []FileEntry `json:\"matches\"`\n281:     Truncated bool        `json:\"truncated\"`\n282: }\n283: \n284: type ChmodRequest struct {\n285:     Path string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n286:     Mode string `json:\"mode\" binding:\"required\"`\n287: }\n288: \n289: type ChmodResponse struct {\n290:     Path string `json:\"path\"`\n291:     Mode string `json:\"mode\"`\n292: }\n293: ```\n294: \n295: ### 2.4 FileManager Implementation Struct\n296: \n297: ```go\n298: type fileManager struct {\n299:     workspaceDir     string\n300:     resolvedWorkspace string\n301:     maxChunkSize     int64\n302:     maxBatchSize     int\n303:     maxSearchResults int\n304:     maxSearchDepth   int\n305:     tempDir          string // for chunked uploads\n306: }\n307: ```\n308: \n309: ### 2.5 Constants (`files/types.go`)\n310: \n311: | Constant | Value | Purpose |\n312: |----------|-------|---------|\n313: | `DefaultMaxChunkSize` | `32 << 20` (33554432) | Default max chunk size (32 MiB) |\n314: | `DefaultMaxBatchSize` | `100` | Default max batch operation size |\n315: | `DefaultMaxSearchResults` | `100` | Default max search results |\n316: | `DefaultMaxSearchDepth` | `50` | Default max directory depth for search |\n317: | `DefaultDirMode` | `\"0755\"` | Default directory creation mode |\n318: | `DefaultFileMode` | `\"0644\"` | Default file creation mode |\n319: | `MaxFileMode` | `0777` | Maximum valid file mode |\n320: | `ChunkExt` | `\".chunk\"` | Suffix for temporary chunk files |\n321: \n322: ### 2.6 Sentinel Errors\n323: \n324: ```go\n325: var (\n326:     ErrPathTraversal     = errors.New(\"access denied: workspace jail violation\")\n327:     ErrFileNotFound      = errors.New(\"file not found\")\n328:     ErrDirectoryNotFound = errors.New(\"directory not found\")\n329:     ErrIsDirectory       = errors.New(\"path is a directory, not a file\")\n330:     ErrNotADirectory     = errors.New(\"path is not a directory\")\n331:     ErrInvalidBase64     = errors.New(\"invalid base64 content\")\n332:     ErrInvalidMode       = errors.New(\"invalid mode format\")\n333:     ErrModeOutOfRange    = errors.New(\"mode exceeds maximum allowed value\")\n334:     ErrChunkTooLarge     = errors.New(\"chunk size exceeds maximum\")\n335:     ErrRangeNotSatisfiable = errors.New(\"range not satisfiable\")\n336:     ErrBatchSizeExceeded = errors.New(\"batch size exceeds maximum\")\n337:     ErrDirectoryNotEmpty = errors.New(\"directory is not empty\")\n338:     ErrPathAlreadyExists = errors.New(\"path already exists as a file\")\n339:     ErrWorkspaceNotInitialized = errors.New(\"workspace directory not initialized\")\n340: )\n341: ```\n342: \n343: ---\n344: \n345: ## 3. API Contracts\n346: \n347: ### 3.1 Route Table\n348: \n349: | Method | Path | Handler | Auth |\n350: |--------|------|---------|------|\n351: | POST | `/api/execute` | ExecuteHandler | JWT |\n352: | POST | `/api/files/read` | ReadFileHandler | JWT |\n353: | POST | `/api/files/write` | WriteFileHandler | JWT |\n354: | GET | `/api/files/stat` | StatFileHandler | JWT |\n355: | GET | `/api/files` | ListFilesHandler | JWT |\n356: | POST | `/api/files/upload` | UploadFileHandler | JWT |\n357: | GET | `/api/files/download` | DownloadFileHandler | JWT |\n358: | POST | `/api/files/delete` | DeleteFileHandler | JWT |\n359: | POST | `/api/files/move` | MoveFileHandler | JWT |\n360: | POST | `/api/files/mkdir` | MkDirHandler | JWT |\n361: | POST | `/api/files/search` | SearchFilesHandler | JWT |\n362: | POST | `/api/files/chmod` | ChmodHandler | JWT |\n363: | GET | `/health` | HealthCheckHandler | None |\n364: \n365: ### 3.2 ReadFile API\n366: \n367: **Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/read`\n368: \n369: **Request Body:**\n370: ```json\n371: {\n372:   \"path\": \"hello.txt\",\n373:   \"offset\": 0,\n374:   \"limit\": -1\n375: }\n376: ```\n377: \n378: **Response Body (200):**\n379: ```json\n380: {\n381:   \"content\": \"<base64 encoded content>\",\n382:   \"total_size\": 13,\n383:   \"read_bytes\": 13\n384: }\n385: ```\n386: \n387: **Behavior:**\n388: - Opens file at sanitized path\n389: - Seeks to `offset` (negative treated as 0)\n390: - Reads up to `limit` bytes; if `limit < 0`, reads to EOF\n391: - Base64-encodes content\n392: - If offset exceeds file size: returns empty content, `read_bytes: 0`\n393: - If path is directory: HTTP 400 `ErrIsDirectory`\n394: - If file not found: HTTP 404 `ErrFileNotFound`\n395: \n396: ### 3.3 WriteFile API\n397: \n398: **Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/write`\n399: \n400: **Request Body:**\n401: ```json\n402: {\n403:   \"path\": \"data.txt\",\n404:   \"content\": \"<base64 encoded>\",\n405:   \"offset\": 0,\n406:   \"mode\": \"overwrite\",\n407:   \"create_parent\": false\n408: }\n409: ```\n410: \n411: **Response Body (200):**\n412: ```json\n413: {\n414:   \"path\": \"data.txt\",\n415:   \"size\": 11,\n416:   \"bytes_written\": 11\n417: }\n418: ```\n419: \n420: **Behavior:**\n421: - Decodes Base64 content\n422: - `mode=\"overwrite\"`, `offset=0`: truncate and replace\n423: - `mode=\"overwrite\"`, `offset>0`: seek to offset, overwrite in place (no truncation beyond written data)\n424: - `mode=\"append\"`: append to end (offset ignored)\n425: - `create_parent=true`: create parent directories with mode 0755\n426: - If path is directory: HTTP 400 `ErrIsDirectory`\n427: - If invalid Base64: HTTP 400 `ErrInvalidBase64`\n428: \n429: ### 3.4 StatFile API\n430: \n431: **Endpoint:** `GET /api/files/stat?path=...`\n432: \n433: **Response Body (200):**\n434: ```json\n435: {\n436:   \"name\": \"test.txt\",\n437:   \"size\": 100,\n438:   \"mode\": \"0644\",\n439:   \"mod_time\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n440:   \"is_dir\": false,\n441:   \"is_symlink\": false\n442: }\n443: ```\n444: \n445: **Behavior:**\n446: - Uses `os.Lstat` to detect symlinks\n447: - Returns metadata for file or directory\n448: - If path not found: HTTP 404 `ErrFileNotFound`\n449: \n450: ### 3.5 ListFiles API\n451: \n452: **Endpoint:** `GET /api/files?path=...`\n453: \n454: **Response Body (200):**\n455: ```json\n456: {\n457:   \"files\": [\n458:     {\"name\": \"src\", \"size\": 4096, \"modified\": \"...\", \"mode\": \"drwxr-xr-x\", \"is_dir\": true},\n459:     {\"name\": \"readme.md\", \"size\": 1024, \"modified\": \"...\", \"mode\": \"-rw-r--r--\", \"is_dir\": false}\n460:   ]\n461: }\n462: ```\n463: \n464: **Behavior:**\n465: - Requires `path` query parameter\n466: - Lists directory contents\n467: - If path missing: HTTP 400\n468: - If path not found: HTTP 404\n469: - If path is not a directory: HTTP 400\n470: \n471: ### 3.6 UploadFile API\n472: \n473: **Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/upload`\n474: \n475: **Content Types:**\n476: - `multipart/form-data`: form fields `path`, `file`, optional `mode`, `chunk_index`, `chunk_total`\n477: - `application/json`: JSON body with `UploadFileRequest` or `ChunkedUploadRequest`\n478: \n479: **Chunked Upload (multipart):**\n480: - Headers: `X-Chunk-Index`, `X-Chunk-Total`\n481: - Form fields: `chunk_index`, `chunk_total`\n482: - Chunks written to `<tempDir>/<path>.chunk.<index>`\n483: - Final chunk triggers merge: concatenate chunks in order, write to final path\n484: - Temp files cleaned up after merge or on error\n485: \n486: **Chunked Upload (JSON):**\n487: - Body includes `chunk_index`, `chunk_total` fields\n488: - Same temp file and merge behavior\n489: \n490: **Chunk Size Validation:**\n491: - If chunk body exceeds `MaxChunkSize`: HTTP 413 `ErrChunkTooLarge`\n492: \n493: ### 3.7 DownloadFile API\n494: \n495: **Endpoint:** `GET /api/files/download?path=...`\n496: \n497: **Range Request Support:**\n498: - If `Range` header present (format: `bytes=start-end`):\n499:   - Parse range\n500:   - If range satisfiable: HTTP 206 with `Content-Range`, partial content\n501:   - If range beyond file size: HTTP 416 `ErrRangeNotSatisfiable`\n502: - If no `Range` header: HTTP 200 with full content\n503: \n504: **Response Headers:**\n505: - `Content-Type`: detected from file extension or `application/octet-stream`\n506: - `Content-Disposition`: `attachment; filename=\"<basename>\"`\n507: - `Content-Description`: `File Transfer`\n508: - `Content-Transfer-Encoding`: `binary`\n509: - For 206: `Content-Range: bytes start-end/total`\n510: \n511: ### 3.8 DeleteFile API\n512: \n513: **Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/delete`\n514: \n515: **Request Body:**\n516: ```json\n517: {\"path\": \"tmp.txt\"}\n518: // or\n519: {\"paths\": [\"a.txt\", \"b.txt\", \"c.txt\"]}\n520: ```\n521: \n522: **Response Body (200):**\n523: ```json\n524: {\n525:   \"deleted\": [\"a.txt\", \"c.txt\"],\n526:   \"failed\": [{\"path\": \"b.txt\", \"error\": \"file not found\"}]\n527: }\n528: ```\n529: \n530: **Behavior:**\n531: - Single `path`: delete one file or empty directory\n532: - `paths`: batch delete up to `MaxBatchSize` entries\n533: - Uses `os.Remove` (not `os.RemoveAll`) вҖ” directories must be empty\n534: - Batch: continues on failure, reports partial results\n535: - If batch exceeds `MaxBatchSize`: HTTP 400 `ErrBatchSizeExceeded`\n536: \n537: ### 3.9 MoveFile API\n538: \n539: **Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/move`\n540: \n541: **Request Body:**\n542: ```json\n543: {\n544:   \"source\": \"old.txt\",\n545:   \"destination\": \"new.txt\"\n546: }\n547: ```\n548: \n549: **Response Body (200):**\n550: ```json\n551: {\n552:   \"source\": \"old.txt\",\n553:   \"destination\": \"new.txt\"\n554: }\n555: ```\n556: \n557: **Behavior:**\n558: - Uses `os.Rename`\n559: - Both source and destination sanitized against workspace\n560: - If source not found: HTTP 404\n561: - If destination parent not found: HTTP 400\n562: - If destination escapes workspace: HTTP 400 `ErrPathTraversal`\n563: \n564: ### 3.10 MkDir API\n565: \n566: **Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/mkdir`\n567: \n568: **Request Body:**\n569: ```json\n570: {\n571:   \"path\": \"a/b/c\",\n572:   \"mode\": \"0755\"\n573: }\n574: ```\n575: \n576: **Response Body (200):**\n577: ```json\n578: {\n579:   \"path\": \"a/b/c\",\n580:   \"created\": true\n581: }\n582: ```\n583: \n584: **Behavior:**\n585: - Uses `os.MkdirAll`\n586: - If directory already exists: `created: false`, no error\n587: - If path is existing file: HTTP 400 `ErrPathAlreadyExists`\n588: - Default mode: `0755`\n589: \n590: ### 3.11 SearchFiles API\n591: \n592: **Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/search`\n593: \n594: **Request Body:**\n595: ```json\n596: {\n597:   \"path\": \"src\",\n598:   \"pattern\": \"*.go\",\n599:   \"max_results\": 50\n600: }\n601: ```\n602: \n603: **Response Body (200):**\n604: ```json\n605: {\n606:   \"matches\": [\n607:     {\"name\": \"main.go\", \"size\": 1024, \"modified\": \"...\", \"mode\": \"-rw-r--r--\", \"is_dir\": false}\n608:   ],\n609:   \"truncated\": false\n610: }\n611: ```\n612: \n613: **Behavior:**\n614: - Uses `filepath.WalkDir` to traverse directory tree\n615: - Matches entry names against `pattern` using `path.Match`\n616: - Respects `MaxSearchDepth` (default 50) вҖ” directories beyond depth skipped\n617: - Results limited to `max_results` (default from config)\n618: - If search root not found: HTTP 404\n619: - If search root is file: HTTP 400 `ErrNotADirectory`\n620: - If invalid glob pattern: HTTP 400\n621: \n622: ### 3.12 Chmod API\n623: \n624: **Endpoint:** `POST /api/files/chmod`\n625: \n626: **Request Body:**\n627: ```json\n628: {\n629:   \"path\": \"script.sh\",\n630:   \"mode\": \"0755\"\n631: }\n632: ```\n633: \n634: **Response Body (200):**\n635: ```json\n636: {\n637:   \"path\": \"script.sh\",\n638:   \"mode\": \"0755\"\n639: }\n640: ```\n641: \n642: **Behavior:**\n643: - Parses octal mode string (base 8)\n644: - Validates mode вүӨ 0777\n645: - Calls `os.Chmod` on sanitized path\n646: - If invalid mode format: HTTP 400 `ErrInvalidMode`\n647: - If mode > 0777: HTTP 400 `ErrModeOutOfRange`\n648: - If path not found: HTTP 404\n649: \n650: ### 3.13 Error Response Format\n651: \n652: All endpoints use consistent error format:\n653: \n654: ```json\n655: {\"error\": \"<human-readable message>\", \"code\": <http_status_code>}\n656: ```\n657: \n658: **HTTP Status Code Matrix:**\n659: \n660: | Code | Condition |\n661: |------|-----------|\n662: | 400 | Invalid request (bad path, bad format, missing required field, path traversal, directory where file expected, invalid mode, invalid glob) |\n663: | 404 | File or directory not found |\n664: | 409 | Conflict (destination exists during move) |\n665: | 413 | Request body or chunk too large |\n666: | 416 | Range not satisfiable |\n667: | 500 | Internal server error (file system operation failure) |\n668: \n669: ### 3.14 Path Sanitization\n670: \n671: All path inputs pass through `sanitizePath`:\n672: \n673: 1. Strip leading `/` from absolute paths\n674: 2. `filepath.Clean` to normalize\n675: 3. Join with resolved workspace directory\n676: 4. Verify result is within workspace via `filepath.Rel`\n677: 5. `filepath.EvalSymlinks` on final candidate\n678: 6. Re-verify symlink-resolved path is within workspace\n679: 7. If any check fails: return `ErrPathTraversal`\n680: \n681: ---\n682: \n683: ## 4. Core Implementation\n684: \n685: ### 4.1 FileManager Constructor\n686: \n687: ```go\n688: func NewFileManager(workspaceDir string, cfg Config) (FileManager, error) {\n689:     resolved, err := filepath.Abs(workspaceDir)\n690:     if err != nil {\n691:         return nil, err\n692:     }\n693:     resolved, err = filepath.EvalSymlinks(resolved)\n694:     if err != nil {\n695:         resolved = filepath.Clean(resolved)\n696:     }\n697: \n698:     if cfg.MaxChunkSize <= 0 {\n699:         cfg.MaxChunkSize = DefaultMaxChunkSize\n700:     }\n701:     if cfg.MaxBatchSize <= 0 {\n702:         cfg.MaxBatchSize = DefaultMaxBatchSize\n703:     }\n704:     if cfg.MaxSearchResults <= 0 {\n705:         cfg.MaxSearchResults = DefaultMaxSearchResults\n706:     }\n707:     if cfg.MaxSearchDepth <= 0 {\n708:         cfg.MaxSearchDepth = DefaultMaxSearchDepth\n709:     }\n710: \n711:     tempDir := filepath.Join(os.TempDir(), \"picod-chunks\")\n712:     if err := os.MkdirAll(tempDir, 0700); err != nil {\n713:         return nil, err\n714:     }\n715: \n716:     return &fileManager{\n717:         workspaceDir:     workspaceDir,\n718:         resolvedWorkspace: resolved,\n719:         maxChunkSize:     cfg.MaxChunkSize,\n720:         maxBatchSize:     cfg.MaxBatchSize,\n721:         maxSearchResults: cfg.MaxSearchResults,\n722:         maxSearchDepth:   cfg.MaxSearchDepth,\n723:         tempDir:          tempDir,\n724:     }, nil\n725: }\n726: ```\n727: \n728: ### 4.2 sanitizePath (`files/sanitize.go`)\n729: \n730: ```go\n731: func (fm *fileManager) sanitizePath(p string) (string, error) {\n732:     if fm.resolvedWorkspace == \"\" {\n733:         return \"\", ErrWorkspaceNotInitialized\n734:     }\n735: \n736:     cleanPath := filepath.Clean(p)\n737:     if filepath.IsAbs(cleanPath) {\n738:         cleanPath = strings.TrimPrefix(cleanPath, string(os.PathSeparator))\n739:     }\n740: \n741:     fullPathCandidate := filepath.Clean(filepath.Join(fm.resolvedWorkspace, cleanPath))\n742: \n743:     relPath, relErr := filepath.Rel(fm.resolvedWorkspace, fullPathCandidate)\n744:     if relErr != nil {\n745:         return \"\", ErrPathTraversal\n746:     }\n747:     sep := string(os.PathSeparator)\n748:     if strings.HasPrefix(relPath, \"..\"+sep) || relPath == \"..\" {\n749:         return \"\", ErrPathTraversal\n750:     }\n751: \n752:     resolvedFinalPath, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(fullPathCandidate)\n753:     if err == nil {\n754:         relPath2, relErr2 := filepath.Rel(fm.resolvedWorkspace, resolvedFinalPath)\n755:         if relErr2 != nil {\n756:             return \"\", ErrPathTraversal\n757:         }\n758:         if strings.HasPrefix(relPath2, \"..\"+sep) || relPath2 == \"..\" {\n759:             return \"\", ErrPathTraversal\n760:         }\n761:         return resolvedFinalPath, nil\n762:     }\n763: \n764:     return fullPathCandidate, nil\n765: }\n766: ```\n767: \n768: ### 4.3 ReadFile Implementation (`files/read.go`)\n769: \n770: ```go\n771: func (fm *fileManager) ReadFile(ctx context.Context, req *ReadFileRequest) (*ReadFileResponse, error) {\n772:     safePath, err := fm.sanitizePath(req.Path)\n773:     if err != nil {\n774:         return nil, err\n775:     }\n776: \n777:     info, err := os.Stat(safePath)\n778:     if err != nil {\n779:         if os.IsNotExist(err) {\n780:             return nil, ErrFileNotFound\n781:         }\n782:         return nil, err\n783:     }\n784:     if info.IsDir() {\n785:         return nil, ErrIsDirectory\n786:     }\n787: \n788:     f, err := os.Open(safePath)\n789:     if err != nil {\n790:         return nil, err\n791:     }\n792:     defer f.Close()\n793: \n794:     totalSize := info.Size()\n795:     offset := req.Offset\n796:     if offset < 0 {\n797:         offset = 0\n798:     }\n799: \n800:     if _, err := f.Seek(offset, io.SeekStart); err != nil {\n801:         return nil, err\n802:     }\n803: \n804:     var data []byte\n805:     if req.Limit < 0 {\n806:         data, err = io.ReadAll(f)\n807:     } else {\n808:         data = make([]byte, req.Limit)\n809:         n, err := f.Read(data)\n810:         data = data[:n]\n811:         if err != nil && err != io.EOF {\n812:             return nil, err\n813:         }\n814:     }\n815: \n816:     return &ReadFileResponse{\n817:         Content:   base64.StdEncoding.EncodeToString(data),\n818:         TotalSize: totalSize,\n819:         ReadBytes: int64(len(data)),\n820:     }, nil\n821: }\n822: ```\n823: \n824: ### 4.4 WriteFile Implementation (`files/write.go`)\n825: \n826: ```go\n827: func (fm *fileManager) WriteFile(ctx context.Context, req *WriteFileRequest) (*WriteFileResponse, error) {\n828:     data, err := base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString(req.Content)\n829:     if err != nil {\n830:         return nil, ErrInvalidBase64\n831:     }\n832: \n833:     safePath, err := fm.sanitizePath(req.Path)\n834:     if err != nil {\n835:         return nil, err\n836:     }\n837: \n838:     info, statErr := os.Stat(safePath)\n839:     if statErr == nil && info.IsDir() {\n840:         return nil, ErrIsDirectory\n841:     }\n842: \n843:     if req.CreateParent {\n844:         if err := os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(safePath), 0755); err != nil {\n845:             return nil, err\n846:         }\n847:     }\n848: \n849:     var flags int\n850:     switch req.Mode {\n851:     case \"append\":\n852:         flags = os.O_CREATE | os.O_WRONLY | os.O_APPEND\n853:     default: // overwrite\n854:         if req.Offset > 0 {\n855:             flags = os.O_CREATE | os.O_WRONLY\n856:         } else {\n857:             flags = os.O_CREATE | os.O_WRONLY | os.O_TRUNC\n858:         }\n859:     }\n860: \n861:     fileMode := parseFileMode(req.Mode)\n862:     f, err := os.OpenFile(safePath, flags, fileMode)\n863:     if err != nil {\n864:         return nil, err\n865:     }\n866:     defer f.Close()\n867: \n868:     if req.Offset > 0 && req.Mode != \"append\" {\n869:         if _, err := f.Seek(req.Offset, io.SeekStart); err != nil {\n870:             return nil, err\n871:         }\n872:     }\n873: \n874:     n, err := f.Write(data)\n875:     if err != nil {\n876:         return nil, err\n877:     }\n878: \n879:     info, err = os.Stat(safePath)\n880:     if err != nil {\n881:         return nil, err\n882:     }\n883: \n884:     relPath, _ := filepath.Rel(fm.workspaceDir, safePath)\n885:     return &WriteFileResponse{\n886:         Path:         relPath,\n887:         Size:         info.Size(),\n888:         BytesWritten: int64(n),\n889:     }, nil\n890: }\n891: ```\n892: \n893: ### 4.5 Chunked Upload (`files/upload.go`)\n894: \n895: ```go\n896: func (fm *fileManager) handleChunkedUpload(ctx context.Context, req *ChunkedUploadRequest) (*FileInfo, error) {\n897:     data, err := base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString(req.Content)\n898:     if err != nil {\n899:         return nil, ErrInvalidBase64\n900:     }\n901: \n902:     if int64(len(data)) > fm.maxChunkSize {\n903:         return nil, ErrChunkTooLarge\n904:     }\n905: \n906:     safePath, err := fm.sanitizePath(req.Path)\n907:     if err != nil {\n908:         return nil, err\n909:     }\n910: \n911:     chunkFileName := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s.chunk.%d\", filepath.Base(safePath), req.ChunkIndex)\n912:     chunkPath := filepath.Join(fm.tempDir, chunkFileName)\n913: \n914:     if err := os.WriteFile(chunkPath, data, 0600); err != nil {\n915:         return nil, err\n916:     }\n917: \n918:     if req.ChunkIndex == req.ChunkTotal-1 {\n919:         return fm.mergeChunks(safePath, req.Path, req.ChunkTotal, parseFileMode(req.Mode))\n920:     }\n921: \n922:     relPath, _ := filepath.Rel(fm.workspaceDir, safePath)\n923:     return &FileInfo{\n924:         Path:     relPath,\n925:         Size:     int64(len(data)),\n926:         Mode:     \"0600\",\n927:         Modified: time.Now(),\n928:     }, nil\n929: }\n930: \n931: func (fm *fileManager) mergeChunks(finalPath, relPath string, totalChunks int, mode os.FileMode) (*FileInfo, error) {\n932:     defer fm.cleanupChunks(relPath, totalChunks)\n933: \n934:     final, err := os.OpenFile(finalPath, os.O_CREATE|os.O_WRONLY|os.O_TRUNC, mode)\n935:     if err != nil {\n936:         return nil, err\n937:     }\n938:     defer final.Close()\n939: \n940:     for i := 0; i < totalChunks; i++ {\n941:         chunkPath := filepath.Join(fm.tempDir, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s.chunk.%d\", filepath.Base(finalPath), i))\n942:         data, err := os.ReadFile(chunkPath)\n943:         if err != nil {\n944:             return nil, err\n945:         }\n946:         if _, err := final.Write(data); err != nil {\n947:             return nil, err\n948:         }\n949:     }\n950: \n951:     info, err := os.Stat(finalPath)\n952:     if err != nil {\n953:         return nil, err\n954:     }\n955: \n956:     relPathResp, _ := filepath.Rel(fm.workspaceDir, finalPath)\n957:     return &FileInfo{\n958:         Path:     relPathResp,\n959:         Size:     info.Size(),\n960:         Mode:     info.Mode().String(),\n961:         Modified: info.ModTime(),\n962:     }, nil\n963: }\n964: \n965: func (fm *fileManager) cleanupChunks(relPath string, totalChunks int) {\n966:     for i := 0; i < totalChunks; i++ {\n967:         chunkPath := filepath.Join(fm.tempDir, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s.chunk.%d\", filepath.Base(relPath), i))\n968:         os.Remove(chunkPath)\n969:     }\n970: }\n971: ```\n972: \n973: ### 4.6 Download with Range Support (`files/download.go`)\n974: \n975: ```go\n976: func (fm *fileManager) DownloadFile(ctx context.Context, req *DownloadFileRequest) (*DownloadFileResponse, error) {\n977:     safePath, err := fm.sanitizePath(req.Path)\n978:     if err != nil {\n979:         return nil, err\n980:     }\n981: \n982:     info, err := os.Stat(safePath)\n983:     if err != nil {\n984:         if os.IsNotExist(err) {\n985:             return nil, ErrFileNotFound\n986:         }\n987:         return nil, err\n988:     }\n989:     if info.IsDir() {\n990:         return nil, ErrIsDirectory\n991:     }\n992: \n993:     f, err := os.Open(safePath)\n994:     if err != nil {\n995:         return nil, err\n996:     }\n997: \n998:     totalSize := info.Size()\n999: \n1000:     if req.Range != \"\" {\n1001:         return fm.handleRangeRequest(f, req.Range, totalSize, safePath)\n1002:     }\n1003: \n1004:     data, err := io.ReadAll(f)\n1005:     f.Close()\n1006:     if err != nil {\n1007:         return nil, err\n1008:     }\n1009: \n1010:     contentType := mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(safePath))\n1011:     if contentType == \"\" {\n1012:         contentType = \"application/octet-stream\"\n1013:     }\n1014: \n1015:     return &DownloadFileResponse{\n1016:         Content:       data,\n1017:         ContentType:   contentType,\n1018:         ContentLength: totalSize,\n1019:         StatusCode:    http.StatusOK,\n1020:     }, nil\n1021: }\n1022: \n1023: func (fm *fileManager) handleRangeRequest(f *os.File, rangeHeader string, totalSize int64, path string) (*DownloadFileResponse, error) {\n1024:     defer f.Close()\n1025: \n1026:     start, end, err := parseRange(rangeHeader, totalSize)\n1027:     if err != nil {\n1028:         return nil, ErrRangeNotSatisfiable\n1029:     }\n1030: \n1031:     if start >= totalSize {\n1032:         return nil, ErrRangeNotSatisfiable\n1033:     }\n1034: \n1035:     if end >= totalSize {\n1036:         end = totalSize - 1\n1037:     }\n1038: \n1039:     length := end - start + 1\n1040:     data := make([]byte, length)\n1041: \n1042:     if _, err := f.Seek(start, io.SeekStart); err != nil {\n1043:         return nil, err\n1044:     }\n1045:     if _, err := io.ReadFull(f, data); err != nil && err != io.ErrUnexpectedEOF {\n1046:         return nil, err\n1047:     }\n1048: \n1049:     contentType := mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(path))\n1050:     if contentType == \"\" {\n1051:         contentType = \"application/octet-stream\"\n1052:     }\n1053: \n1054:     return &DownloadFileResponse{\n1055:         Content:       data,\n1056:         ContentType:   contentType,\n1057:         ContentLength: length,\n1058:         StatusCode:    http.StatusPartialContent,\n1059:         ContentRange:  fmt.Sprintf(\"bytes %d-%d/%d\", start, end, totalSize),\n1060:     }, nil\n1061: }\n1062: \n1063: func parseRange(rangeHeader string, totalSize int64) (int64, int64, error) {\n1064:     if !strings.HasPrefix(rangeHeader, \"bytes=\") {\n1065:         return 0, 0, errors.New(\"invalid range format\")\n1066:     }\n1067: \n1068:     rangeSpec := strings.TrimPrefix(rangeHeader, \"bytes=\")\n1069:     parts := strings.SplitN(rangeSpec, \"-\", 2)\n1070:     if len(parts) != 2 {\n1071:         return 0, 0, errors.New(\"invalid range format\")\n1072:     }\n1073: \n1074:     start, err := strconv.ParseInt(parts[0], 10, 64)\n1075:     if err != nil {\n1076:         return 0, 0, err\n1077:     }\n1078: \n1079:     var end int64\n1080:     if parts[1] == \"\" {\n1081:         end = totalSize - 1\n1082:     } else {\n1083:         end, err = strconv.ParseInt(parts[1], 10, 64)\n1084:         if err != nil {\n1085:             return 0, 0, err\n1086:         }\n1087:     }\n1088: \n1089:     if start > end {\n1090:         return 0, 0, errors.New(\"invalid range: start > end\")\n1091:     }\n1092: \n1093:     return start, end, nil\n1094: }\n1095: ```\n1096: \n1097: ### 4.7 SearchFiles Implementation (`files/search.go`)\n1098: \n1099: ```go\n1100: func (fm *fileManager) SearchFiles(ctx context.Context, req *SearchFilesRequest) (*SearchFilesResponse, error) {\n1101:     safePath, err := fm.sanitizePath(req.Path)\n1102:     if err != nil {\n1103:         return nil, err\n1104:     }\n1105: \n1106:     info, err := os.Stat(safePath)\n1107:     if err != nil {\n1108:         if os.IsNotExist(err) {\n1109:             return nil, ErrDirectoryNotFound\n1110:         }\n1111:         return nil, err\n1112:     }\n1113:     if !info.IsDir() {\n1114:         return nil, ErrNotADirectory\n1115:     }\n1116: \n1117:     maxResults := req.MaxResults\n1118:     if maxResults <= 0 {\n1119:         maxResults = fm.maxSearchResults\n1120:     }\n1121: \n1122:     baseDepth := strings.Count(safePath, string(os.PathSeparator))\n1123: \n1124:     var matches []FileEntry\n1125:     var truncated bool\n1126: \n1127:     err = filepath.WalkDir(safePath, func(path string, d os.DirEntry, err error) error {\n1128:         if err != nil {\n1129:             return err\n1130:         }\n1131: \n1132:         depth := strings.Count(path, string(os.PathSeparator)) - baseDepth\n1133:         if depth > fm.maxSearchDepth {\n1134:             return filepath.SkipDir\n1135:         }\n1136: \n1137:         matched, matchErr := path.Match(req.Pattern, d.Name())\n1138:         if matchErr != nil {\n1139:             return matchErr\n1140:         }\n1141: \n1142:         if matched && !d.IsDir() {\n1143:             info, err := d.Info()\n1144:             if err != nil {\n1145:                 return nil\n1146:             }\n1147: \n1148:             relPath, _ := filepath.Rel(fm.workspaceDir, path)\n1149:             matches = append(matches, FileEntry{\n1150:                 Name:     relPath,\n1151:                 Size:     info.Size(),\n1152:                 Modified: info.ModTime(),\n1153:                 Mode:     info.Mode().String(),\n1154:                 IsDir:    false,\n1155:             })\n1156: \n1157:             if len(matches) >= maxResults {\n1158:                 truncated = true\n1159:                 return errors.New(\"search complete\")\n1160:             }\n1161:         }\n1162: \n1163:         return nil\n1164:     })\n1165: \n1166:     if err != nil && err.Error() != \"search complete\" {\n1167:         return nil, err\n1168:     }\n1169: \n1170:     return &SearchFilesResponse{\n1171:         Matches:   matches,\n1172:         Truncated: truncated,\n1173:     }, nil\n1174: }\n1175: ```\n1176: \n1177: ### 4.8 Server Route Registration (updated `server.go`)\n1178: \n1179: ```go\n1180: func (s *Server) registerRoutes() {\n1181:     fm, err := files.NewFileManager(s.workspaceDir, s.config.FileConfig)\n1182:     if err != nil {\n1183:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create file manager: %v\", err)\n1184:     }\n1185:     s.fileManager = fm\n1186: \n1187:     api := s.engine.Group(\"/api\")\n1188:     api.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n1189:     {\n1190:         api.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)\n1191: \n1192:         fileGroup := api.Group(\"/files\")\n1193:         {\n1194:             fileGroup.POST(\"/read\", s.ReadFileHandler)\n1195:             fileGroup.POST(\"/write\", s.WriteFileHandler)\n1196:             fileGroup.GET(\"/stat\", s.StatFileHandler)\n1197:             fileGroup.GET(\"\", s.ListFilesHandler)\n1198:             fileGroup.POST(\"/upload\", s.UploadFileHandler)\n1199:             fileGroup.GET(\"/download\", s.DownloadFileHandler)\n1200:             fileGroup.POST(\"/delete\", s.DeleteFileHandler)\n1201:             fileGroup.POST(\"/move\", s.MoveFileHandler)\n1202:             fileGroup.POST(\"/mkdir\", s.MkDirHandler)\n1203:             fileGroup.POST(\"/search\", s.SearchFilesHandler)\n1204:             fileGroup.POST(\"/chmod\", s.ChmodHandler)\n1205:         }\n1206:     }\n1207:     s.engine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n1208: }\n1209: ```\n1210: \n1211: ### 4.9 Config Extension (`config.go`)\n1212: \n1213: ```go\n1214: type FileConfig struct {\n1215:     MaxChunkSize     int64 `json:\"max_chunk_size\"`\n1216:     MaxBatchSize     int   `json:\"max_batch_size\"`\n1217:     MaxSearchResults int   `json:\"max_search_results\"`\n1218:     MaxSearchDepth   int   `json:\"max_search_depth\"`\n1219: }\n1220: \n1221: type Config struct {\n1222:     Port      int        `json:\"port\"`\n1223:     Workspace string     `json:\"workspace\"`\n1224:     FileConfig FileConfig `json:\"file_config\"`\n1225: }\n1226: \n1227: func ParseFlags() Config {\n1228:     port := flag.Int(\"port\", 8080, \"Port for the PicoD server to listen on\")\n1229:     workspace := flag.String(\"workspace\", \"\", \"Root directory for file operations\")\n1230:     maxChunkSize := flag.Int64(\"max-chunk-size\", files.DefaultMaxChunkSize, \"Maximum size per chunk in bytes\")\n1231:     maxBatchSize := flag.Int(\"max-batch-size\", files.DefaultMaxBatchSize, \"Maximum number of paths in batch operations\")\n1232:     maxSearchResults := flag.Int(\"max-search-results\", files.DefaultMaxSearchResults, \"Maximum search results\")\n1233:     maxSearchDepth := flag.Int(\"max-search-depth\", files.DefaultMaxSearchDepth, \"Maximum directory depth for search\")\n1234:     flag.Parse()\n1235: \n1236:     return Config{\n1237:         Port:      *port,\n1238:         Workspace: *workspace,\n1239:         FileConfig: FileConfig{\n1240:             MaxChunkSize:     *maxChunkSize,\n1241:             MaxBatchSize:     *maxBatchSize,\n1242:             MaxSearchResults: *maxSearchResults,\n1243:             MaxSearchDepth:   *maxSearchDepth,\n1244:         },\n1245:     }\n1246: }\n1247: ```\n1248: \n1249: ---\n1250: \n1251: ## 5. Environment Variables\n1252: \n1253: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n1254: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n1255: | `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` | Yes | вҖ” | RSA public key for JWT verification |\n1256: | `PICOD_WORKSPACE` | No | cwd | Default workspace directory |\n1257: | `PICOD_PORT` | No | 8080 | Server listen port |\n1258: \n1259: File management limits are configured via CLI flags, not environment variables.\n1260: \n1261: ---\n1262: \n1263: ## 6. Testing Strategy\n1264: \n1265: ### 6.1 Unit Test Matrix\n1266: \n1267: #### Config Tests (`config_test.go`)\n1268: \n1269: | Test Name | Description |\n1270: |-----------|-------------|\n1271: | `TestParseFlags_Defaults` | No flags вҶ’ default values for all fields |\n1272: | `TestParseFlags_CustomFileLimits` | `--max-chunk-size=16777216 --max-batch-size=50` вҶ’ reflected in config |\n1273: | `TestParseFlags_CustomSearchLimits` | `--max-search-results=200 --max-search-depth=20` вҶ’ reflected in config |\n1274: \n1275: #### FileManager Tests (`files/manager_test.go`)\n1276: \n1277: | Test Name | Description |\n1278: |-----------|-------------|\n1279: | `TestNewFileManager_Defaults` | Zero config вҶ’ default limits applied |\n1280: | `TestNewFileManager_CustomConfig` | Custom config вҶ’ limits reflected |\n1281: | `TestNewFileManager_InvalidWorkspace` | Non-existent workspace вҶ’ error |\n1282: \n1283: #### Sanitize Tests (`files/sanitize_test.go`)\n1284: \n1285: | Test Name | Description |\n1286: |-----------|-------------|\n1287: | `TestSanitizePath_NormalPath` | `hello.txt` вҶ’ workspace/hello.txt |\n1288: | `TestSanitizePath_Subdirectory` | `src/main.go` вҶ’ workspace/src/main.go |\n1289: | `TestSanitizePath_AbsolutePath` | `/etc/passwd` вҶ’ workspace/etc/passwd |\n1290: | `TestSanitizePath_ParentTraversal` | `../../etc/passwd` вҶ’ ErrPathTraversal |\n1291: | `TestSanitizePath_SymlinkEscape` | Symlink pointing outside workspace вҶ’ ErrPathTraversal |\n1292: | `TestSanitizePath_EmptyPath` | `\"\"` вҶ’ workspace root |\n1293: \n1294: #### ReadFile Tests (`files/read_test.go`)\n1295: \n1296: | Test Name | Description |\n1297: |-----------|-------------|\n1298: | `TestReadFile_EntireFile` | Read full file вҶ’ Base64 content, total_size, read_bytes |\n1299: | `TestReadFile_WithOffset` | offset=7 вҶ’ content from offset |\n1300: | `TestReadFile_WithOffsetAndLimit` | offset=7, limit=5 вҶ’ 5 bytes from offset |\n1301: | `TestReadFile_OffsetExceedsSize` | offset > file size вҶ’ empty content, read_bytes=0 |\n1302: | `TestReadFile_LimitExceedsRemaining` | limit > remaining bytes вҶ’ read to EOF |\n1303: | `TestReadFile_NegativeOffset` | offset=-1 вҶ’ treated as 0 |\n1304: | `TestReadFile_Directory` | path is directory вҶ’ HTTP 400 |\n1305: | `TestReadFile_NotFound` | path doesn't exist вҶ’ HTTP 404 |\n1306: | `TestReadFile_PathTraversal` | `../../etc/passwd` вҶ’ HTTP 400 |\n1307: \n1308: #### WriteFile Tests (`files/write_test.go`)\n1309: \n1310: | Test Name | Description |\n1311: |-----------|-------------|\n1312: | `TestWriteFile_Overwrite` | Replace file content |\n1313: | `TestWriteFile_Append` | Append to existing file |\n1314: | `TestWriteFile_AtOffset` | Write at specific offset without truncation |\n1315: | `TestWriteFile_CreateParent` | `create_parent=true` вҶ’ directories created |\n1316: | `TestWriteFile_NoCreateParent` | `create_parent=false`, missing parent вҶ’ error |\n1317: | `TestWriteFile_InvalidBase64` | Invalid base64 вҶ’ HTTP 400 |\n1318: | `TestWriteFile_ToDirectory` | Path is directory вҶ’ HTTP 400 |\n1319: \n1320: #### StatFile Tests (`files/stat_test.go`)\n1321: \n1322: | Test Name | Description |\n1323: |-----------|-------------|\n1324: | `TestStatFile_RegularFile` | File metadata returned |\n1325: | `TestStatFile_Directory` | `is_dir: true` |\n1326: | `TestStatFile_Symlink` | `is_symlink: true` |\n1327: | `TestStatFile_NotFound` | HTTP 404 |\n1328: | `TestStatFile_PathTraversal` | HTTP 400 |\n1329: \n1330: #### ListFiles Tests (`files/list_test.go`)\n1331: \n1332: | Test Name | Description |\n1333: |-----------|-------------|\n1334: | `TestListFiles_DirectoryContents` | Returns file entries |\n1335: | `TestListFiles_MissingPath` | HTTP 400 |\n1336: | `TestListFiles_NotFound` | HTTP 404 |\n1337: | `TestListFiles_NotDirectory` | HTTP 400 |\n1338: \n1339: #### Upload Tests (`files/upload_test.go`)\n1340: \n1341: | Test Name | Description |\n1342: |-----------|-------------|\n1343: | `TestUpload_Multipart` | Multipart form upload |\n1344: | `TestUpload_JSONBase64` | JSON body with Base64 content |\n1345: | `TestUpload_ChunkedSingle` | Single chunk (no chunk headers) вҶ’ direct write |\n1346: | `TestUpload_ChunkedMulti` | 3 chunks вҶ’ merged correctly |\n1347: | `TestUpload_ChunkedOutOfOrder` | Chunks 2,0,1 вҶ’ assembled in order 0,1,2 |\n1348: | `TestUpload_ChunkExceedsMax` | Chunk > MaxChunkSize вҶ’ HTTP 413 |\n1349: | `TestUpload_ChunkCleanup` | After merge, no .chunk.* files remain |\n1350: \n1351: #### Download Tests (`files/download_test.go`)\n1352: \n1353: | Test Name | Description |\n1354: |-----------|-------------|\n1355: | `TestDownload_FullFile` | No Range header вҶ’ HTTP 200, full content |\n1356: | `TestDownload_RangePartial` | `Range: bytes=0-499` вҶ’ HTTP 206, Content-Range |\n1357: | `TestDownload_RangeToEOF` | `Range: bytes=500-` вҶ’ bytes 500 to end |\n1358: | `TestDownload_RangeBeyondSize` | `Range: bytes=200-300` on 100-byte file вҶ’ HTTP 416 |\n1359: | `TestDownload_Directory` | HTTP 400 |\n1360: | `TestDownload_NotFound` | HTTP 404 |\n1361: \n1362: #### Delete Tests (`files/delete_test.go`)\n1363: \n1364: | Test Name | Description |\n1365: |-----------|-------------|\n1366: | `TestDelete_SingleFile` | Delete one file |\n1367: | `TestDelete_SingleNotFound` | HTTP 404 |\n1368: | `TestDelete_BatchAllSuccess` | Multiple files deleted |\n1369: | `TestDelete_BatchPartialFailure` | Some succeed, some fail вҶ’ partial results |\n1370: | `TestDelete_BatchExceedsMax` | > MaxBatchSize вҶ’ HTTP 400 |\n1371: | `TestDelete_NonEmptyDirectory` | HTTP 400 |\n1372: | `TestDelete_EmptyDirectory` | Success |\n1373: \n1374: #### Move Tests (`files/move_test.go`)\n1375: \n1376: | Test Name | Description |\n1377: |-----------|-------------|\n1378: | `TestMove_RenameFile` | Rename within same directory |\n1379: | `TestMove_MoveToSubdirectory` | Move to existing subdirectory |\n1380: | `TestMove_SourceNotFound` | HTTP 404 |\n1381: | `TestMove_DestParentNotFound` | HTTP 400 |\n1382: | `TestMove_EscapeWorkspace` | Destination escapes workspace вҶ’ HTTP 400 |\n1383: \n1384: #### MkDir Tests (`files/mkdir_test.go`)\n1385: \n1386: | Test Name | Description |\n1387: |-----------|-------------|\n1388: | `TestMkDir_CreateNew` | New directory created, `created: true` |\n1389: | `TestMkDir_AlreadyExists` | Directory exists, `created: false` |\n1390: | `TestMkDir_CustomMode` | Mode 0700 applied |\n1391: | `TestMkDir_PathIsFile` | HTTP 400 |\n1392: \n1393: #### Search Tests (`files/search_test.go`)\n1394: \n1395: | Test Name | Description |\n1396: |-----------|-------------|\n1397: | `TestSearch_FindFiles` | Glob pattern matches files |\n1398: | `TestSearch_RecursiveGlob` | Pattern matches in subdirectories |\n1399: | `TestSearch_Truncated` | Results limited to max_results, `truncated: true` |\n1400: | `TestSearch_NoMatches` | Empty matches, `truncated: false` |\n1401: | `TestSearch_RootNotFound` | HTTP 404 |\n1402: | `TestSearch_RootIsFile` | HTTP 400 |\n1403: | `TestSearch_InvalidPattern` | HTTP 400 |\n1404: | `TestSearch_DepthLimit` | Directories beyond MaxSearchDepth skipped |\n1405: \n1406: #### Chmod Tests (`files/chmod_test.go`)\n1407: \n1408: | Test Name | Description |\n1409: |-----------|-------------|\n1410: | `TestChmod_ChangePermissions` | Mode changed successfully |\n1411: | `TestChmod_InvalidMode` | HTTP 400 |\n1412: | `TestChmod_ModeOutOfRange` | `07777` вҶ’ HTTP 400 |\n1413: | `TestChmod_NotFound` | HTTP 404 |\n1414: \n1415: #### Server Integration Tests (`server_test.go`)\n1416: \n1417: | Test Name | Description |\n1418: |-----------|-------------|\n1419: | `TestServer_RoutesRegistered` | All 11 file management routes exist |\n1420: | `TestServer_LegacyRoutesRemoved` | `POST /api/files` вҶ’ 404/400, `GET /api/files/*` вҶ’ 404 |\n1421: | `TestServer_HealthCheck` | `/health` returns 200 |\n1422: | `TestServer_AuthRequired` | Requests without JWT вҶ’ 401 |\n1423: \n1424: ### 6.2 Test Helpers\n1425: \n1426: ```go\n1427: func setupTestWorkspace(t *testing.T) (string, func()) {\n1428:     dir := t.TempDir()\n1429:     return dir, func() {}\n1430: }\n1431: \n1432: func createTestFile(t *testing.T, workspace, relPath, content string) string {\n1433:     fullPath := filepath.Join(workspace, relPath)\n1434:     os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(fullPath), 0755)\n1435:     os.WriteFile(fullPath, []byte(content), 0644)\n1436:     return fullPath\n1437: }\n1438: \n1439: func newTestServer(t *testing.T, workspace string) *httptest.Server {\n1440:     cfg := Config{\n1441:         Port:      0,\n1442:         Workspace: workspace,\n1443:         FileConfig: FileConfig{\n1444:             MaxChunkSize:     files.DefaultMaxChunkSize,\n1445:             MaxBatchSize:     files.DefaultMaxBatchSize,\n1446:             MaxSearchResults: files.DefaultMaxSearchResults,\n1447:             MaxSearchDepth:   files.DefaultMaxSearchDepth,\n1448:         },\n1449:     }\n1450:     // Note: tests may need to mock JWT auth or use test keys\n1451:     s := NewServer(cfg)\n1452:     return httptest.NewServer(s.engine)\n1453: }\n1454: \n1455: func performJSONRequest(method, url string, body interface{}) *http.Response {\n1456:     var buf bytes.Buffer\n1457:     if body != nil {\n1458:         json.NewEncoder(&buf).Encode(body)\n1459:     }\n1460:     req, _ := http.NewRequest(method, url, &buf)\n1461:     req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n1462:     // Add JWT token header for auth\n1463:     return http.DefaultClient.Do(req)\n1464: }\n1465: ```\n1466: \n1467: ### 6.3 Mock Strategy\n1468: \n1469: - **Filesystem:** Use `t.TempDir()` for isolated test workspaces\n1470: - **JWT Auth:** Generate test RSA key pairs for signing/verification\n1471: - **Chunked Upload:** Write test chunks directly to temp directory, verify merge\n1472: - **Symlink Tests:** Create symlinks within test workspace pointing to known targets\n1473: \n1474: ### 6.4 Gate Requirements\n1475: \n1476: 1. `go build ./pkg/picod/...` compiles\n1477: 2. `go vet ./pkg/picod/...` produces no warnings\n1478: 3. `go test ./pkg/picod/... -v` all pass\n1479: 4. `go test -race ./pkg/picod/...` no data race warnings\n1480: 5. `go mod tidy` results in no changes\n1481: 6. All new handlers have unit tests covering normal, error, and edge cases\n1482: 7. Legacy AR-015 tests continue to pass (upload, list, download, sanitize)\n1483: \n1484: ---\n1485: \n1486: ## 7. Deployment Considerations\n1487: \n1488: 1. **Workspace Jail:** The workspace directory must be an absolute path. Symlinks in the workspace path are resolved at startup. All file operations are constrained within the resolved workspace.\n1489: \n1490: 2. **Chunked Upload Temp Directory:** Temporary chunk files are stored in `<os.TempDir>/picod-chunks/`. Ensure sufficient disk space for concurrent chunked uploads. Temp files are cleaned up after merge or on error.\n1491: \n1492: 3. **MaxChunkSize:** Default 32 MiB. For large file transfers, clients should split into smaller chunks. The server validates each chunk size independently.\n1493: \n1494: 4. **MaxBatchSize:** Default 100. Batch delete operations continue on individual failures and report partial results. No atomicity guarantee across batch entries.\n1495: \n1496: 5. **Search Depth Limit:** Default 50 levels. Prevents stack overflow or excessive traversal on deeply nested directory structures.\n1497: \n1498: 6. **File Mode Validation:** Mode strings are parsed as octal (base 8). Maximum valid mode is 0777. Modes exceeding this are rejected.\n1499: \n1500: ---\n1501: \n1502: ## 8. Implementation Steps\n1503: \n1504: ### Phase 1: Subpackage Scaffolding (Day 1)\n1505: \n1506: 1. Create `pkg/picod/files/` directory structure\n1507: 2. Define `FileManager` interface in `manager.go`\n1508: 3. Migrate `sanitizePath` to `files/sanitize.go`\n1509: 4. Move request/response types to `files/types.go`\n1510: 5. Write `sanitize_test.go` (migrate from existing tests)\n1511: \n1512: ### Phase 2: Core File Operations (Day 2)\n1513: \n1514: 1. Implement `ReadFile` in `read.go` + tests\n1515: 2. Implement `WriteFile` in `write.go` + tests\n1516: 3. Implement `StatFile` in `stat.go` + tests\n1517: 4. Migrate `ListFiles` to `list.go` + tests\n1518: 5. Update `Config` struct with file management fields\n1519: \n1520: ### Phase 3: Upload/Download with Advanced Features (Day 3)\n1521: \n1522: 1. Migrate `UploadFile` to `upload.go` with chunk support + tests\n1523: 2. Migrate `DownloadFile` to `download.go` with Range support + tests\n1524: 3. Implement `DeleteFile` in `delete.go` with batch support + tests\n1525: 4. Implement `MoveFile` in `move.go` + tests\n1526: \n1527: ### Phase 4: Utility Operations (Day 4)\n1528: \n1529: 1. Implement `MkDir` in `mkdir.go` + tests\n1530: 2. Implement `SearchFiles` in `search.go` + tests\n1531: 3. Implement `Chmod` in `chmod.go` + tests\n1532: 4. Update `server.go` route registration\n1533: 5. Update `config.go` with CLI flags\n1534: \n1535: ### Phase 5: Integration & Gate (Day 5)\n1536: \n1537: 1. Run `go build ./pkg/picod/...`\n1538: 2. Run `go vet ./pkg/picod/...`\n1539: 3. Run `go test ./pkg/picod/... -v`\n1540: 4. Run `go test -race ./pkg/picod/...`\n1541: 5. Run `go mod tidy`\n1542: 6. Verify legacy AR-015 tests pass\n1543: 7. Remove old `files.go`\n1544: \n1545: ---\n1546: \n1547: ## 9. Future Changes\n1548: \n1549: | Change | Description | Priority |\n1550: |--------|-------------|----------|\n1551: | AR-0XX | File watch/tail API for real-time content streaming | P2 |\n1552: | AR-0XX | Archive download (tar/zip) for directory downloads | P2 |\n1553: | AR-0XX | File copy/duplicate API | P3 |\n1554: | AR-0XX | Recursive directory delete (`os.RemoveAll`) with safety guard | P3 |\n1555: | AR-0XX | File content diff API | P3 |\n1556: \n1557: ### Known Limitations\n1558: \n1559: - Batch delete is not atomic; partial failures are reported but not rolled back\n1560: - Chunked uploads require all chunks to arrive; no resume support for interrupted uploads\n1561: - Search uses `filepath.WalkDir` which is synchronous; large directories may block the handler\n1562: - No file locking; concurrent writes to the same file may cause data corruption\n1563: - Symlink following is limited to the final path resolution; intermediate symlinks within the workspace are followed\n\n(End of file - total 1563 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-016: PicoD File Management API вҖ” Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThe `pkg/picod/files/` subpackage provides a comprehensive file management API for the PicoD in-sandbox daemon. It replaces the monolithic `files.go` with a structured subpackage that exports a `FileManager` interface and individual HTTP handlers for read, write, stat, list, upload, download, delete, move, mkdir, search, and chmod operations. All operations are constrained within a workspace jail via path sanitization and protected by JWT authentication.\n\n### 1.2 Route Reorganization\n\nThe file management routes are reorganized from legacy wildcard/overloaded paths to explicit sub-paths under `/api/files/`:\n\n```\nLegacy (AR-015)                  вҶ’  AR-016\nв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nPOST /api/files (upload)         вҶ’  POST /api/files/upload\nGET  /api/files (list)           вҶ’  GET  /api/files (with ?path query)\nGET  /api/files/*path (download) вҶ’  GET  /api/files/download?path=...\n                                  +  POST /api/files/read\n                                  +  POST /api/files/write","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775848151116,"end":1775848151124}}}}
