{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848346601,"sessionID":"ses_287348949ffemSMrps0exZh022","part":{"id":"prt_d78ccc67d001px81oVcw3BHqOu","messageID":"msg_d78cc9b62001jIt3cf864KkLRF","sessionID":"ses_287348949ffemSMrps0exZh022","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_9a982bfe25f842ca9e9b339d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-019 вҖ” CLI дәҢиҝӣеҲ¶е…ҘеҸЈ (4 binaries) вҖ” Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nAgentCube з”ұ 4 дёӘзӢ¬з«Ӣзҡ„ Go дәҢиҝӣеҲ¶з»„жҲҗпјҢеҗ„иҮӘжүҝжӢ…жҳҺзЎ®зҡ„иҝҗиЎҢж—¶иҒҢиҙЈпјҡ\n\n| Binary | Package | Role | Pattern |\n|--------|---------|------|---------|\n| `agentd` | `cmd/agentd` | Sandbox CR жҺ§еҲ¶еҷЁпјҢзӣ‘еҗ¬ Sandbox иө„жәҗеҸҳеҢ–е№¶и°ғи°җ Pod з”ҹе‘Ҫе‘Ёжңҹ | controller-runtime reconciler |\n| `picod` | `cmd/picod` | жІҷз®ұеҶ…е®ҲжҠӨиҝӣзЁӢпјҢжҸҗдҫӣд»Јз Ғжү§иЎҢ + ж–Үд»¶з®ЎзҗҶ API | standalone HTTP server (gin) |\n| `workloadmanager` | `cmd/workloadmanager` | жІҷз®ұзј–жҺ’ API жңҚеҠЎпјҡеҲӣе»ә/еҲ йҷӨ/еҲ—иЎЁ/зҠ¶жҖҒ/TTL з»ӯжңҹ + GC жё…зҗҶ | HTTP API + informer-based reconciler |\n| `router` | `cmd/router` | еҸҚеҗ‘д»ЈзҗҶзҪ‘е…іпјҡJWT йүҙжқғ вҶ’ session жҹҘжүҫ вҶ’ иҜ·жұӮиҪ¬еҸ‘еҲ°жІҷз®ұ Pod | HTTP reverse proxy + informer-driven routing |\n\nеӣӣиҖ…йҖҡиҝҮ Kubernetes APIпјҲCRD + informersпјүе’Ңе…ұдә« storeпјҲRedis/ValkeyпјүеҚҸеҗҢпјҢж— зӣҙжҺҘиҝӣзЁӢй—ҙйҖҡдҝЎгҖӮ\n\n### 1.2 Package Layout\n\n```\ncmd/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ agentd/\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ main.go                  вҖ” controller-runtime manager + Sandbox reconciler\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ picod/\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ main.go                  вҖ” ParseFlags вҶ’ NewServer вҶ’ Run\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ workloadmanager/\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ main.go                  вҖ” [TODO] CLI entry point\nв””в”Җв”Җ router/\n    в””в”Җв”Җ main.go                  вҖ” [TODO] CLI entry point\n\npkg/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ agentd/                      вҖ” agentd business logic (existing)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ reconciler.go\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ reconciler_test.go\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ const.go\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ picod/                       вҖ” picod business logic (existing)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ server.go\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ config.go\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ types.go\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ auth.go\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ execute.go\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ files.go\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ files/                   вҖ” file management subpackage\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ workloadmanager/             вҖ” workload manager business logic (existing)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ reconciler/\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ reconciler.go        вҖ” SandboxReconciler (informer + workqueue)\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ types.go             вҖ” ReconcilerDeps, Store interface, constants\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ sync.go\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ pod.go\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ agentruntime.go\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ codeinterpreter.go\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ event_handlers.go\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ metrics.go\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ handler/\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ sandbox_lifecycle.go вҖ” LifecycleManager (GC, status, list, extend TTL)\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ sandbox_create.go    вҖ” SandboxCreateHandler (create AR/CI sandboxes)\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ sandbox_delete.go    вҖ” SandboxDeleteHandler\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ models.go            вҖ” Request/Response types, SandboxInfo\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ constants.go         вҖ” GVRs, labels, annotations\nв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ sandbox_lifecycle_test.go\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ response/\nв”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ response.go          вҖ” HTTP response helpers\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ router/                      вҖ” router business logic (existing)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ server.go                вҖ” Server struct, route registration, Start/Run/Shutdown\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ config.go                вҖ” Config, NewDefaultConfig\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ proxy.go                 вҖ” handleInvoke, forwardToSandbox (reverse proxy)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ router.go                вҖ” Router interface + implementation\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ backend.go               вҖ” Backend struct\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ loadbalancer.go          вҖ” LoadBalancer interface\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ informer.go              вҖ” InformerManager (watches AR/CI CRs)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ middleware.go            вҖ” Auth, concurrency limit\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ jwt.go                   вҖ” JWTManager (RS256)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ session_manager.go       вҖ” SessionManager (store-backed)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ health.go                вҖ” Health check handlers\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ errors.go                вҖ” Error types\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ config_test.go, server_test.go, ...\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ store/                       вҖ” shared store abstraction (Redis/Valkey)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ store.go\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ singleton.go\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ codec.go\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ store_redis.go\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ store_valkey.go\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ apis/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ runtime/v1alpha1/        вҖ” AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter CR types\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ agents/v1alpha1/         вҖ” Sandbox CR types\nв””в”Җв”Җ common/types/\n    в””в”Җв”Җ types.go                 вҖ” shared type constants\n```\n\n### 1.3 Data Flow\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                              Kubernetes Cluster                              в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  agentd      в”Ӯ   в”Ӯworkloadmgr   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   router     в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   picod      в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ (controller) в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ  (API srv)   в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ  (proxy)     в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ (in-sandbox) в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ         в”Ӯ                  в”Ӯ                  в”Ӯ                  в”Ӯ           в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    watches             CRUD on            reads session      serves API     в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    Sandbox             Sandbox CRs        info from store    on PodIP       в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    CRs                 creates/deletes                        в”Ӯ              в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    вҶ’ reconciles        sandboxes          в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ           в”Ӯ           в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    вҶ’ manages Pods      в”Ӯ                  в”Ӯ store в”Ӯв—„в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ           в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                        в”Ӯ                  в”Ӯ(Redis)в”Ӯ  entryPoints           в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                        в–ј                  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ                        в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ              в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ              в”Ӯ                            в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ              в”Ӯ  LifecycleMgr   в”Ӯ              в”Ӯ session lookup             в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ              в”Ӯ  (GC: TTL/idle/ в”Ӯ              в”Ӯ + JWT forward              в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ              в”Ӯ   orphan/ghost) в”Ӯ              в”Ӯ                            в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ              в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ              в–ј                            в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                                               Client HTTP   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                                                    в”Ӯ        в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                                                                     в”Ӯ\n                        Client вҶ’ router (JWT auth) вҶ’ proxy вҶ’ picod вҶҗв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n**е…ій”®дәӨдә’и·Ҝеҫ„пјҡ**\n\n1. **еҲӣе»әжІҷз®ұ**пјҡClient вҶ’ `workloadmanager` API вҶ’ еҲӣе»ә Sandbox CR вҶ’ `agentd` и°ғи°җ вҶ’ Pod еҗҜеҠЁ вҶ’ `picod` е°ұз»Ә вҶ’ `workloadmanager` еҶҷе…Ҙ storeпјҲentryPointsпјү\n2. **иҜ·жұӮжІҷз®ұ**пјҡClient вҶ’ `router`пјҲJWT йүҙжқғпјүвҶ’ жҹҘ store иҺ·еҸ– session вҶ’ еҸҚеҗ‘д»ЈзҗҶеҲ° Pod IP:Port вҶ’ `picod`\n3. **жё…зҗҶжІҷз®ұ**пјҡ`workloadmanager.LifecycleManager` е®ҡж—¶ GC вҶ’ еҲ йҷӨиҝҮжңҹ/з©әй—І Sandbox CR вҶ’ `agentd` и°ғи°җеҲ йҷӨ Pod\n\n### 1.4 Dependencies\n\n| Binary | Direct Dependencies | Purpose |\n|--------|-------------------|---------|\n| `agentd` | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime`, `k8s.io/api/core/v1`, `pkg/apis/agents/v1alpha1` | Controller-runtime manager, Sandbox CR scheme |\n| `picod` | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin`, `k8s.io/klog/v2` | HTTP server, structured logging |\n| `workloadmanager` | `client-go/clientset`, `client-go/informers`, `client-go/listers`, `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic`, `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes`, `pkg/store`, `pkg/workloadmanager/*` | Typed client, informers, dynamic client, store, handlers |\n| `router` | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin`, `client-go/clientset`, `client-go/informers`, `pkg/store`, `pkg/router/*` | HTTP proxy, informer-driven routing, store-backed sessions |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 `workloadmanager` вҖ” CLI Config\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port                  string\n    Debug                 bool\n    Kubeconfig            string\n    Namespace             string\n    Workers               int\n    StoreType             string\n    StoreAddr             string\n    StorePassword         string\n    StoreDB               int\n    SessionCheckInterval  time.Duration\n    SessionIdleTimeout    time.Duration\n    SessionMaxDuration    time.Duration\n    EnableAuth            bool\n    MetricsPort           string\n}\n\nfunc NewDefaultConfig() *Config {\n    return &Config{\n        Port:                  \"8080\",\n        Debug:                 false,\n        Kubeconfig:            \"\",\n        Namespace:             \"\",\n        Workers:               2,\n        StoreType:             \"redis\",\n        StoreAddr:             \"localhost:6379\",\n        StoreDB:               0,\n        SessionCheckInterval:  5 * time.Minute,\n        SessionIdleTimeout:    30 * time.Minute,\n        SessionMaxDuration:    24 * time.Hour,\n        EnableAuth:            false,\n        MetricsPort:           \"9090\",\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 2.2 `router` вҖ” CLI Config\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port                  string\n    Debug                 bool\n    EnableTLS             bool\n    TLSCert               string\n    TLSKey                string\n    MaxConcurrentRequests int\n    Kubeconfig            string\n    Namespace             string\n    SessionCheckInterval  time.Duration\n    SessionIdleTimeout    time.Duration\n    SessionMaxDuration    time.Duration\n    StoreType             string\n    StoreAddr             string\n    StorePassword         string\n    StoreDB               int\n    JWTExpiration         time.Duration\n    JWTIssuer             string\n    JWTLeeway             time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n`router.Config` е·ІеӯҳеңЁдәҺ `pkg/router/config.go`пјҢдёҺ `NewDefaultConfig()` еҜ№йҪҗгҖӮ\n\n### 2.3 Shared Types (reference from existing packages)\n\n| Type | Source | Used By |\n|------|--------|---------|\n| `SandboxInfo` | `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/models.go` | workloadmanager, router (via store) |\n| `CreateSandboxRequest` | `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/models.go` | workloadmanager |\n| `CreateSandboxResponse` | `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/models.go` | workloadmanager |\n| `EntryPoint` | `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/models.go` | workloadmanager, router |\n| `ReconcilerDeps` | `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/types.go` | workloadmanager |\n| `Store` (interface) | `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/types.go` + `pkg/store/` | workloadmanager, router |\n| `Config` (router) | `pkg/router/config.go` | router |\n| `JWTConfig` | `pkg/router/config.go` | router |\n\n### 2.4 Constants\n\n```go\n// From pkg/workloadmanager/handler/constants.go\nvar (\n    AgentRuntimeGVR    = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"agentruntimes\"}\n    CodeInterpreterGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"codeinterpreters\"}\n    SandboxGVR         = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\"}\n    SandboxClaimGVR    = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\"}\n)\n\nconst (\n    LabelManagedBy      = \"app.kubernetes.io/managed-by\"\n    LabelManagedByValue = \"agentcube-workload-manager\"\n    LabelSessionID      = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n    LabelWorkloadName   = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\n    LabelSandboxName    = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 `workloadmanager` HTTP API\n\n| Method | Path | Handler | Auth | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|------|-------------|\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | `CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox` / `CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox` | Optional (Bearer token) | Create sandbox from AR/CI template |\n| `DELETE` | `/api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID` | `DeleteSandbox` | Optional | Delete sandbox by session ID |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID` | `GetSandboxStatus` | Optional | Get sandbox status |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | `ListSandboxes` | Optional | List sandboxes (?namespace=&status=) |\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/sandboxes/:sessionID/extend` | `ExtendSandboxTTL` | Optional | Extend sandbox TTL |\n| `GET` | `/health/live` | `handleHealthLive` | None | Liveness probe |\n| `GET` | `/health/ready` | `handleHealthReady` | None | Readiness probe |\n\n**Create Sandbox Request:**\n```json\n{\n  \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n  \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\"\n}\n```\n\n**Create Sandbox Response (200):**\n```json\n{\n  \"sessionId\": \"uuid-v4\",\n  \"sandboxId\": \"k8s-uid\",\n  \"sandboxName\": \"my-agent-abc12345\",\n  \"entryPoints\": [\n    {\"path\": \"/\", \"protocol\": \"HTTP\", \"endpoint\": \"10.0.0.1:8080\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### 3.2 `router` HTTP API\n\n| Method | Path | Handler | Auth | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|------|-------------|\n| `GET` | `/health/live` | `handleHealthLive` | None | Liveness probe |\n| `GET` | `/health/ready` | `handleHealthReady` | None | Readiness probe |\n| `GET/POST` | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | `handleAgentInvoke` | JWT (RS256) | Proxy to AgentRuntime sandbox |\n| `GET/POST` | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` | JWT (RS256) | Proxy to CodeInterpreter sandbox |\n\n**Proxy Flow:**\n1. Extract `namespace` + `name` from URL path\n2. Extract `x-agentcube-session-id` header (optional вҖ” creates new session if absent)\n3. Look up or create session via `SessionManager` (store-backed)\n4. Resolve sandbox `entryPoints` from CR template or store\n5. Select entry point by path prefix match\n6. Reverse proxy request to `PodIP:Port` via `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy`\n7. Inject `X-Forwarded-*` headers + `x-agentcube-session-id` response header\n8. Update `LastActivityAt` in store\n\n### 3.3 `agentd` вҖ” No HTTP API\n\n`agentd` is a pure controller-runtime manager. It exposes:\n- **Metrics**: disabled (`BindAddress: \"0\"`)\n- **Health probes**: disabled (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`)\n\nCommunication is entirely via Kubernetes API (watch/reconcile Sandbox CRs).\n\n### 3.4 `picod` HTTP API\n\n| Method | Path | Handler | Auth | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|------|-------------|\n| `POST` | `/api/execute` | `ExecuteHandler` | JWT | Execute code in sandbox |\n| `POST` | `/api/files/read` | `ReadFileHandler` | JWT | Read file content (Base64) |\n| `POST` | `/api/files/write` | `WriteFileHandler` | JWT | Write file content (Base64) |\n| `GET` | `/api/files/stat` | `StatFileHandler` | JWT | File metadata |\n| `GET` | `/api/files` | `ListFilesHandler` | JWT | List directory |\n| `POST` | `/api/files/upload` | `UploadFileHandler` | JWT | Upload file (multipart/JSON) |\n| `GET` | `/api/files/download` | `DownloadFileHandler` | JWT | Download file (Range support) |\n| `POST` | `/api/files/delete` | `DeleteFileHandler` | JWT | Delete file(s) |\n| `POST` | `/api/files/move` | `MoveFileHandler` | JWT | Move/rename file |\n| `POST` | `/api/files/mkdir` | `MkDirHandler` | JWT | Create directory |\n| `POST` | `/api/files/search` | `SearchFilesHandler` | JWT | Search files by glob |\n| `POST` | `/api/files/chmod` | `ChmodHandler` | JWT | Change file permissions |\n| `GET` | `/health` | `HealthCheckHandler` | None | Health check |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Core Implementation\n\n### 4.1 `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n    \"flag\"\n    \"fmt\"\n    \"net/http\"\n    \"os\"\n    \"os/signal\"\n    \"syscall\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n    \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/handler\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/response\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n    cfg := parseFlags()\n\n    klog.InitFlags(nil)\n    if cfg.Debug {\n        flag.Set(\"v\", \"4\")\n    }\n\n    restConfig, err := buildKubeConfig(cfg.Kubeconfig)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to build kubeconfig: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    kubeClientset, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(restConfig)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create kubernetes clientset: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    dynamicClient, err := dynamic.NewForConfig(restConfig)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create dynamic client: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    acClientset, err := clientset.NewForConfig(restConfig)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create agentcube clientset: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    informerFactory := externalversions.NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(\n        ac_clientset,\n        30*time.Second,\n        externalversions.WithNamespace(cfg.Namespace),\n    )\n\n    arLister := informerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Lister()\n    ciLister := informerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Lister()\n\n    store.Init(&store.Config{\n        Type:     cfg.StoreType,\n        Address:  cfg.StoreAddr,\n        Password: cfg.StorePassword,\n        DB:       cfg.StoreDB,\n    })\n    storeClient := store.Storage()\n\n    reconcilerDeps := reconciler.ReconcilerDeps{\n        Clientset:       acClientset,\n        InformerFactory: informerFactory,\n        ARLister:        arLister,\n        CILister:        ciLister,\n        Store:           storeClient,\n        Workers:         cfg.Workers,\n    }\n    sandboxReconciler := reconciler.NewSandboxReconciler(reconcilerDeps)\n\n    lifecycleDeps := &handler.LifecycleManagerDeps{\n        DynamicClient:      dynamicClient,\n        Store:              storeClient,\n        CheckInterval:      cfg.SessionCheckInterval,\n        DefaultTTL:         cfg.SessionMaxDuration,\n        DefaultIdleTimeout: cfg.SessionIdleTimeout,\n    }\n    lifecycleManager := handler.NewLifecycleManager(lifecycleDeps)\n\n    createHandlerDeps := &handler.SandboxCreateHandlerDeps{\n        DynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n        Clientset:       acClientset,\n        KubeClientset:   kubeClientset,\n        InformerFactory: informerFactory,\n        Store:           storeClient,\n        Reconciler:      sandboxReconciler,\n        EnableAuth:      cfg.EnableAuth,\n    }\n    createHandler := handler.NewSandboxCreateHandler(createHandlerDeps)\n\n    deleteHandlerDeps := &handler.SandboxDeleteHandlerDeps{\n        DynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n        Store:           storeClient,\n        InformerFactory: informerFactory,\n        EnableAuth:      cfg.EnableAuth,\n    }\n    deleteHandler := handler.NewSandboxDeleteHandler(deleteHandlerDeps)\n\n    stopCh := make(chan struct{})\n    go sandboxReconciler.Run(stopCh)\n\n    ctx := signalHandlerContext()\n    go lifecycleManager.Start(ctx)\n\n    if cfg.Debug {\n        gin.SetMode(gin.DebugMode)\n    } else {\n        gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)\n    }\n    engine := gin.New()\n    engine.Use(gin.Recovery())\n\n    engine.GET(\"/health/live\", handleLive)\n    engine.GET(\"/health/ready\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n        response.JSON(c, http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n    })\n\n    v1 := engine.Group(\"/api/v1\")\n    v1.POST(\"/sandboxes\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n        var req handler.CreateSandboxRequest\n        if err := c.ShouldBindJSON(&req); err != nil {\n            response.Error(c, http.StatusBadRequest, http.StatusBadRequest, \"Invalid request body\")\n            return\n        }\n        switch req.Kind {\n        case handler.AgentRuntimeKind:\n            createHandler.CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(c)\n        case handler.CodeInterpreterKind:\n            createHandler.CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox(c)\n        default:\n            response.Error(c, http.StatusBadRequest, http.StatusBadRequest,\n                fmt.Sprintf(\"invalid kind %q\", req.Kind))\n        }\n    })\n    v1.DELETE(\"/sandboxes/:sessionID\", deleteHandler.DeleteSandbox)\n    v1.GET(\"/sandboxes/:sessionID\", lifecycleManager.GetSandboxStatus)\n    v1.GET(\"/sandboxes\", lifecycleManager.ListSandboxes)\n    v1.POST(\"/sandboxes/:sessionID/extend\", lifecycleManager.ExtendSandboxTTL)\n\n    server := &http.Server{\n        Addr:    \":\" + cfg.Port,\n        Handler: engine,\n    }\n\n    go func() {\n        klog.Infof(\"workloadmanager listening on %s\", cfg.Port)\n        if err := server.ListenAndServe(); err != nil && err != http.ErrServerClosed {\n            klog.Fatalf(\"server failed: %v\", err)\n        }\n    }()\n\n    <-ctx.Done()\n    klog.Info(\"shutting down workloadmanager...\")\n    close(stopCh)\n    lifecycleManager.Stop()\n    server.Shutdown(ctx)\n}\n```\n\n### 4.2 `cmd/router/main.go`\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n    \"flag\"\n    \"os\"\n    \"os/signal\"\n    \"syscall\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n    \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n    cfg := parseFlags()\n\n    klog.InitFlags(nil)\n\n    restConfig, err := buildKubeConfig(cfg.Kubeconfig)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to build kubeconfig: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    acClientset, err := clientset.NewForConfig(restConfig)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create agentcube clientset: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    store.Init(&store.Config{\n        Type:     cfg.StoreType,\n        Address:  cfg.StoreAddr,\n        Password: cfg.StorePassword,\n        DB:       cfg.StoreDB,\n    })\n\n    server, err := router.NewServer(&router.Config{\n        Port:                  cfg.Port,\n        Debug:                 cfg.Debug,\n        EnableTLS:             cfg.EnableTLS,\n        TLSCert:               cfg.TLSCert,\n        TLSKey:                cfg.TLSKey,\n        MaxConcurrentRequests: cfg.MaxConcurrentRequests,\n        SessionCheckInterval:  cfg.SessionCheckInterval,\n        SessionIdleTimeout:    cfg.SessionIdleTimeout,\n        SessionMaxDuration:    cfg.SessionMaxDuration,\n        StoreType:             cfg.StoreType,\n        JWTExpiration:         cfg.JWTExpiration,\n        JWTIssuer:             cfg.JWTIssuer,\n        JWTLeeway:             cfg.JWTLeeway,\n    })\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create router server: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    informerManager := router.NewInformerManager(acClientset, server.GetRouter())\n    stopCh := make(chan struct{})\n    go informerManager.Start(stopCh)\n\n    go server.Run()\n\n    sigCh := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n    signal.Notify(sigCh, syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\n    <-sigCh\n\n    klog.Info(\"shutting down router...\")\n    close(stopCh)\n}\n```\n\n### 4.3 Flag Parsing\n\n**`workloadmanager` flags:**\n\n| Flag | Env | Default | Description |\n|------|-----|---------|-------------|\n| `--port` | `WM_PORT` | `8080` | HTTP listen port |\n| `--debug` | `WM_DEBUG` | `false` | Debug mode (verbose logging) |\n| `--kubeconfig` | `KUBECONFIG` | in-cluster | Path to kubeconfig |\n| `--namespace` | `WM_NAMESPACE` | `\"\"` (all) | Watch namespace scope |\n| `--workers` | `WM_WORKERS` | `2` | Reconciler worker count |\n| `--store-type` | `WM_STORE_TYPE` | `redis` | Store backend (`redis`/`valkey`) |\n| `--store-addr` | `WM_STORE_ADDR` | `localhost:6379` | Store address |\n| `--store-password` | `WM_STORE_PASSWORD` | `\"\"` | Store password |\n| `--store-db` | `WM_STORE_DB` | `0` | Store DB index |\n| `--session-check-interval` | `WM_SESSION_CHECK_INTERVAL` | `5m` | GC check interval |\n| `--session-idle-timeout` | `WM_SESSION_IDLE_TIMEOUT` | `30m` | Idle timeout |\n| `--session-max-duration` | `WM_SESSION_MAX_DURATION` | `24h` | Max session TTL |\n| `--enable-auth` | `WM_ENABLE_AUTH` | `false` | Enable Bearer token auth |\n\n**`router` flags:**\n\n| Flag | Env | Default | Description |\n|------|-----|---------|-------------|\n| `--port` | `ROUTER_PORT` | `8080` | HTTP listen port |\n| `--debug` | `ROUTER_DEBUG` | `false` | Debug mode |\n| `--enable-tls` | `ROUTER_ENABLE_TLS` | `false` | Enable HTTPS |\n| `--tls-cert` | `ROUTER_TLS_CERT` | `\"\"` | TLS certificate path |\n| `--tls-key` | `ROUTER_TLS_KEY` | `\"\"` | TLS key path |\n| `--max-concurrent-requests` | `ROUTER_MAX_CONCURRENT` | `1000` | Concurrency limit |\n| `--kubeconfig` | `KUBECONFIG` | in-cluster | Path to kubeconfig |\n| `--namespace` | `ROUTER_NAMESPACE` | `\"\"` (all) | Watch namespace scope |\n| `--store-type` | `ROUTER_STORE_TYPE` | `redis` | Store backend |\n| `--store-addr` | `ROUTER_STORE_ADDR` | `localhost:6379` | Store address |\n| `--store-password` | `ROUTER_STORE_PASSWORD` | `\"\"` | Store password |\n| `--store-db` | `ROUTER_STORE_DB` | `0` | Store DB index |\n| `--jwt-expiration` | `ROUTER_JWT_EXPIRATION` | `5m` | JWT token TTL |\n| `--jwt-issuer` | `ROUTER_JWT_ISSUER` | `agentcube-router` | JWT issuer claim |\n| `--jwt-leeway` | `ROUTER_JWT_LEEWAY` | `1m` | JWT clock skew leeway |\n\n### 4.4 Kubeconfig Resolution\n\nBoth `workloadmanager` and `router` use the same resolution strategy:\n\n```go\nfunc buildKubeConfig(kubeconfig string) (*rest.Config, error) {\n    if kubeconfig != \"\" {\n        return clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", kubeconfig)\n    }\n    if cfg, err := rest.InClusterConfig(); err == nil {\n        return cfg, nil\n    }\n    return clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", clientcmd.RecommendedHomeFile)\n}\n```\n\nPriority: explicit flag вҶ’ in-cluster config вҶ’ `~/.kube/config`.\n\n### 4.5 Store Initialization\n\nStore is a singleton initialized at startup via `pkg/store`:\n\n```go\n// pkg/store/singleton.go\nvar (\n    singleton Store\n    once      sync.Once\n)\n\nfunc Init(cfg *Config) {\n    once.Do(func() {\n        switch cfg.Type {\n        case \"valkey\":\n            singleton = NewValkeyStore(cfg)\n        default:\n            singleton = NewRedisStore(cfg)\n        }\n    })\n}\n\nfunc Storage() Store {\n    return singleton\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Error Handling\n\n### 5.1 Error Categories\n\n| Category | Binary | Strategy |\n|----------|--------|----------|\n| Startup failure | All | `klog.Fatalf` + `os.Exit(1)` вҖ” non-recoverable |\n| Kubeconfig failure | workloadmanager, router | Fatal exit вҖ” cannot function without K8s access |\n| Store connection failure | workloadmanager, router | Fatal exit on init; retry on runtime (store client handles reconnect) |\n| Informer cache sync timeout | workloadmanager, router | Log error, continue вҖ” degraded mode (stale data) |\n| Reconciler error | workloadmanager | Requeue with exponential backoff (5s вҶ’ 5min, max 15 retries) |\n| Sandbox creation timeout | workloadmanager | Rollback CR deletion, return 500 to client |\n| Proxy backend unreachable | router | Return 502 `{\"error\": \"sandbox unreachable\"}` |\n| Proxy timeout | router | Return 504 `{\"error\": \"sandbox timeout\"}` |\n| JWT validation failure | router | Return 401 вҖ” request rejected |\n| GC cleanup failure | workloadmanager | Log error, continue to next entry вҖ” no abort |\n\n### 5.2 Graceful Shutdown\n\n| Binary | Shutdown Sequence |\n|--------|------------------|\n| `agentd` | `ctrl.SetupSignalHandler()` вҶ’ manager.Stop() вҶ’ reconciler finalizers |\n| `picod` | `SIGINT/SIGTERM` вҶ’ `server.Shutdown(ctx)` with 10s timeout |\n| `workloadmanager` | Signal вҶ’ `close(stopCh)` (reconciler) вҶ’ `lifecycleManager.Stop()` вҶ’ HTTP server graceful shutdown |\n| `router` | Signal вҶ’ `close(stopCh)` (informers) вҶ’ `server.Shutdown(ctx)` |\n\n### 5.3 Sentinel Errors\n\n```go\n// router/session_manager.go\ntype SessionNotFoundError struct { SessionID string }\ntype SandboxTemplateNotFoundError struct { Namespace, Name, Kind string }\n\n// workloadmanager handler\nvar (\n    ErrPathTraversal     = errors.New(\"access denied: workspace jail violation\")\n    ErrFileNotFound      = errors.New(\"file not found\")\n    // ... (from picod/files/)\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Testing Strategy\n\n### 6.1 Unit Test Matrix\n\n#### `cmd/workloadmanager/main_test.go`\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestParseFlags_Defaults` | No flags вҶ’ default config values |\n| `TestParseFlags_CustomValues` | All flags set вҶ’ reflected in config |\n| `TestParseFlags_EnvOverrides` | Environment variables override defaults |\n| `TestBuildKubeConfig_InCluster` | In-cluster config when no flag + in-cluster env |\n| `TestBuildKubeConfig_ExplicitPath` | Explicit kubeconfig path takes priority |\n\n#### `cmd/router/main_test.go`\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestParseFlags_Defaults` | No flags вҶ’ default config values |\n| `TestParseFlags_CustomValues` | All flags set вҶ’ reflected in config |\n| `TestParseFlags_TLSConfig` | `--enable-tls --tls-cert --tls-key` вҶ’ TLS config populated |\n| `TestParseFlags_JWTConfig` | JWT flags вҶ’ correct durations and issuer |\n\n### 6.2 Integration Test Strategy\n\n- **E2E sandbox lifecycle**: Use `envtest` (controller-runtime) to spin up a local API server, create AR/CI CRs, verify reconciler behavior\n- **Store mocking**: Use `miniredis` (already in `go.mod` as `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2`) for Redis-backed tests\n- **Proxy tests**: Use `httptest.NewServer` as fake picod backend, verify router forwards correctly with JWT\n- **Flag parsing isolation**: Test `parseFlags()` with isolated `flag.FlagSet` to avoid global state pollution\n\n### 6.3 Gate Requirements\n\n1. `go build ./cmd/...` compiles all 4 binaries\n2. `go vet ./cmd/...` produces no warnings\n3. `go test ./cmd/... -v` all pass\n4. `go test -race ./cmd/...` no data race warnings\n5. `go mod tidy` results in no changes\n6. Each binary's `main.go` вүӨ 100 lines (logic delegated to `pkg/`)\n7. Flag parsing tests cover defaults, custom values, and env overrides\n\n---\n\n## 7. Deployment Considerations\n\n### 7.1 Container Images\n\n| Binary | Image | Run As | Port |\n|--------|-------|--------|------|\n| `agentd` | `agentcube-agentd` | Non-root (65534) | None (controller) |\n| `picod` | Built into sandbox image | User-defined | 8080 (configurable) |\n| `workloadmanager` | `agentcube-workloadmanager` | Non-root (65534) | 8080 |\n| `router` | `agentcube-router` | Non-root (65534) | 8080 |\n\n### 7.2 RBAC Requirements\n\n| Binary | Resources | Verbs |\n|--------|-----------|-------|\n| `agentd` | `sandboxes`, `sandboxclaims`, `pods`, `events` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n| `workloadmanager` | `agentruntimes`, `codeinterpreters`, `sandboxes`, `sandboxclaims`, `pods`, `secrets` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `delete` |\n| `router` | `agentruntimes`, `codeinterpreters`, `secrets` (read public key) | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n\n### 7.3 Resource Limits\n\n| Binary | CPU Request | Memory Request | CPU Limit | Memory Limit |\n|--------|------------|----------------|-----------|--------------|\n| `agentd` | 100m | 128Mi | 500m | 512Mi |\n| `workloadmanager` | 100m | 128Mi | 500m | 512Mi |\n| `router` | 200m | 256Mi | 1000m | 1Gi |\n\n### 7.4 Store Dependency\n\nBoth `workloadmanager` and `router` require a Redis/Valkey instance. The store connection is established at startup; failure is fatal. For production:\n- Use Redis Sentinel or Valkey Cluster for HA\n- Configure `--store-password` via Kubernetes Secret\n- Set appropriate `--store-db` to isolate environments\n\n### 7.5 Metrics\n\n- `workloadmanager`: Reconciler metrics (total, duration, errors, workqueue depth), GC metrics (cleanup total, duration, errors)\n- `router`: Request latency, proxy errors, JWT validation failures, concurrent request count\n- Metrics exposed on separate port (`--metrics-port`, default `9090`) via Prometheus `/metrics` endpoint\n\n---\n\n## 8. Implementation Steps\n\n### Phase 1: `workloadmanager` CLI Entry (Day 1)\n\n1. Create `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n2. Implement `parseFlags()` with env fallback\n3. Implement `buildKubeConfig()` helper\n4. Wire up: kube clients вҶ’ informer factory вҶ’ store вҶ’ reconciler вҶ’ lifecycle manager вҶ’ HTTP server\n5. Add graceful shutdown (signal вҶ’ stopCh вҶ’ lifecycle stop вҶ’ server shutdown)\n6. Write `main_test.go` (flag parsing, kubeconfig resolution)\n\n### Phase 2: `router` CLI Entry (Day 2)\n\n1. Create `cmd/router/main.go`\n2. Implement `parseFlags()` with env fallback\n3. Wire up: kube client вҶ’ store вҶ’ `router.NewServer()` вҶ’ `InformerManager` вҶ’ `server.Run()`\n4. Add graceful shutdown (signal вҶ’ informer stop вҶ’ server shutdown)\n5. Write `main_test.go` (flag parsing, TLS config, JWT config)\n\n### Phase 3: Build & Verification (Day 3)\n\n1. `go build ./cmd/...` вҖ” all 4 binaries compile\n2. `go vet ./cmd/...` вҖ” no warnings\n3. `go test ./cmd/... -v` вҖ” all tests pass\n4. `go test -race ./cmd/...` вҖ” no races\n5. `go mod tidy` вҖ” no changes\n6. Verify binary sizes and startup times\n\n### Phase 4: Dockerfile & Deployment (Day 4)\n\n1. Create multi-stage Dockerfiles for `workloadmanager` and `router`\n2. Add Helm chart templates for new deployments\n3. Document RBAC, resource limits, and env vars\n\n---\n\n## 9. Future Changes\n\n| Change | Description | Priority |\n|--------|-------------|----------|\n| AR-0XX | Unified `agentcube` CLI binary with subcommands (`agentcube agentd`, `agentcube router`, etc.) | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Prometheus metrics endpoint for all binaries | P1 |\n| AR-0XX | Structured logging (zap/slog) across all binaries | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Health probe endpoints for `agentd` (currently disabled) | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | `workloadmanager` warm pool management API for CodeInterpreters | P1 |\n| AR-0XX | Router dynamic route registration from informer events (currently placeholder) | P1 |\n\n### Known Limitations\n\n- `router.InformerManager` event handlers are stubs (`klog.V(4).Infof`) вҖ” dynamic route registration not yet implemented\n- `agentd` has metrics and health probes disabled вҖ” observability gap\n- No mutual TLS between `router` and `picod` вҖ” JWT provides auth but not transport security\n- `workloadmanager` and `router` share the same store instance вҖ” no isolation if one corrupts data\n- Flag parsing uses global `flag` package вҖ” not testable in isolation without `flag.NewFlagSet`\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-019/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/event_handlers.go\">\nERROR [105:28] undefined: LabelSandboxName\nERROR [130:31] undefined: LabelSandboxName\nERROR [164:103] undefined: LabelSandboxName\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/pod.go\">\nERROR [31:28] undefined: LabelSandboxName\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime.go\">\nERROR [51:25] undefined: LabelSessionID\nERROR [77:29] undefined: LabelSandboxName\nERROR [78:29] undefined: LabelWorkloadName\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/codeinterpreter.go\">\nERROR [11:2] \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\" imported as metav1 and not used\nERROR [32:25] undefined: LabelSessionID\nERROR [58:29] undefined: LabelSandboxName\nERROR [59:29] undefined: LabelWorkloadName\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/reconciler.go\">\nERROR [78:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value in argument to runtime.HandleCrash\nERROR [83:24] cannot use (func() literal) (value of type func()) as func(interface{}) value 